1
00:00:05,985 --> 00:00:07,987
[uplifting instrumental music playing]

2
00:00:15,161 --> 00:00:16,203
[music swells]

3
00:00:27,465 --> 00:00:29,467
[music continues]

4
00:00:52,865 --> 00:00:54,867
[music continues]

5
00:01:08,589 --> 00:01:09,840
[music speeds up]

6
00:01:28,859 --> 00:01:30,194
[music swells]

7
00:01:30,277 --> 00:01:33,155
-[music continues on computer]
-[girl] There we go!

8
00:01:33,239 --> 00:01:35,616
-That dress!
-[boy 1] So beautiful. So many people…

9
00:01:35,699 --> 00:01:36,909
-[music stops]
-[gasps]

10
00:01:36,992 --> 00:01:38,244
No!

11
00:01:38,327 --> 00:01:39,870
Why is there a lag?

12
00:01:39,954 --> 00:01:41,956
[boy 1] Our Internet's that bad, huh?

13
00:01:42,039 --> 00:01:44,166
Hey, don't let my uncle hear you.

14
00:01:44,250 --> 00:01:46,752
He's only just bought the latest plan.

15
00:01:46,836 --> 00:01:48,337
Is someone downloading?

16
00:01:48,420 --> 00:01:49,797
Downloading?

17
00:01:49,880 --> 00:01:53,759
-[boy 2] Uh, that's it.
-Hey, it's Ms. Berta. Hi, Ms. Berta.

18
00:01:53,843 --> 00:01:54,844
-[Berta] Hi.
-[boys] You!

19
00:01:54,927 --> 00:01:56,470
-[boy 2] It's him.
-[boy 3] There you go.

20
00:01:58,139 --> 00:01:59,348
-[boy 4] Hey.
-What's that?

21
00:01:59,431 --> 00:02:00,933
I'm trying to burn a CD.

22
00:02:01,016 --> 00:02:02,184
-Oh, are you?
-Yeah.

23
00:02:02,268 --> 00:02:03,727
-Try later.
-What?

24
00:02:03,811 --> 00:02:06,564
Later. We're watching
the debut party for Mara San Andres.

25
00:02:06,647 --> 00:02:08,274
-Uh, what do I care?
-What?

26
00:02:08,357 --> 00:02:10,734
-Why should I care?
-This. This is why you should care.

27
00:02:10,818 --> 00:02:12,069
-[boy 3] That did it!
-Ugh.

28
00:02:12,153 --> 00:02:14,029
-[boy1] Rose.
-[boy 3] Come on, it's on.

29
00:02:14,113 --> 00:02:16,240
-Come on. Hurry, here, hurry!
-Here we are.

30
00:02:16,740 --> 00:02:17,992
-Almost…
-[Rose gasps]

31
00:02:18,075 --> 00:02:20,035
[boy 2] There she is, there she is!

32
00:02:20,536 --> 00:02:23,372
-[Rose] Look at her, she's beautiful!
-[boy 1] Wow!

33
00:02:24,790 --> 00:02:26,667
-[boy 2] Oh!
-[all] Yeah!

34
00:02:26,750 --> 00:02:28,085
-[boy 3] Oh!
-[music stops]

35
00:02:28,169 --> 00:02:29,753
-[all gasp]
-Jeez!

36
00:02:29,837 --> 00:02:30,838
No!

37
00:02:30,921 --> 00:02:32,923
[uplifting instrumental music playing]

38
00:02:40,389 --> 00:02:41,348
[music fades]

39
00:02:41,432 --> 00:02:44,435
[woman] Hey, Jordan,
wipe that frown off your face.

40
00:02:45,102 --> 00:02:47,897
[Jordan] Mom, I still don't understand
what the heck we're doing here.

41
00:02:47,980 --> 00:02:50,691
New job! New opportunities!

42
00:02:50,774 --> 00:02:54,570
Aunt Kakai has offered me
the chance to manage her resort.

43
00:02:57,698 --> 00:03:01,076
-[Jordan exhales deeply] Yeah.
-[indistinct background chatter]

44
00:03:03,329 --> 00:03:06,332
-Are we staying with Aunt Kakai?
-No.

45
00:03:06,415 --> 00:03:08,626
We're renting a house near the resort.

46
00:03:08,709 --> 00:03:09,877
Is there a computer there?

47
00:03:09,960 --> 00:03:12,880
-Probably not.
-Mom, how am I supposed to contact Dad?

48
00:03:12,963 --> 00:03:14,757
There might be a computer shop nearby.

49
00:03:14,840 --> 00:03:18,219
And will you let those shades go?
The sun's gone.

50
00:03:18,302 --> 00:03:19,595
Honestly.

51
00:03:20,554 --> 00:03:21,764
[boy] Oh my God, girls!

52
00:03:22,264 --> 00:03:26,685
I spy with my pretty eyes
a white chocolate wearing a black jacket!

53
00:03:26,769 --> 00:03:29,563
-[girl] Who, where?
-[boy screams in excitement] Shocker!

54
00:03:29,647 --> 00:03:31,232
-[screaming]
-[energetic music playing]

55
00:03:31,315 --> 00:03:32,816
[boy] Baby boy.

56
00:03:35,653 --> 00:03:37,947
-[woman] Jordan!
-[Jordan] Coming.

57
00:03:40,199 --> 00:03:41,200
[music stops]

58
00:03:41,283 --> 00:03:45,287
You're hot! Oh, yes, you are, you cutie.

59
00:03:45,371 --> 00:03:48,749
You don't always dress up,
but you're pretty. Ah!

60
00:03:54,296 --> 00:03:55,339
Darling.

61
00:03:55,839 --> 00:03:58,217
That face of yours is staying the same.

62
00:03:58,300 --> 00:04:01,428
So there's no point
looking at the mirror! [laughs]

63
00:04:01,512 --> 00:04:04,723
Oh, you… You're ruining it.

64
00:04:05,516 --> 00:04:10,396
Your pretty face won't change, all right?
You didn't even let me finish.

65
00:04:10,479 --> 00:04:13,357
-Really? Good recovery!
-Yeah, you like that?

66
00:04:13,440 --> 00:04:14,650
It's just your hair.

67
00:04:14,733 --> 00:04:17,444
It's nice but it looks like
it could be stuck to your forehead.

68
00:04:17,528 --> 00:04:18,654
-Looks greasy.
-Oh. No.

69
00:04:18,737 --> 00:04:21,323
Maybe there's something
I can buy you that'll fix it.

70
00:04:21,407 --> 00:04:24,493
When I'm in town, I can pick up
shampoo, conditioner, whatever.

71
00:04:24,576 --> 00:04:25,869
Thanks, Dad.

72
00:04:25,953 --> 00:04:28,455
I'm gonna buy them myself
'cause today I get paid.

73
00:04:28,539 --> 00:04:32,209
Hang on. You told me
you were saving for your debut.

74
00:04:32,293 --> 00:04:35,629
-Well, I am.
-So why don't you let me buy them?

75
00:04:35,713 --> 00:04:37,339
-Huh?
-Promise?

76
00:04:37,423 --> 00:04:41,260
-Sure! [laughs]
-Really? Oh, you're the best dad ever!

77
00:04:41,343 --> 00:04:43,637
-Thank you, Dad. Thank you!
-I love you!

78
00:04:43,721 --> 00:04:45,306
-I love you!
-You're welcome!

79
00:04:45,389 --> 00:04:47,057
[upbeat music playing]

80
00:05:00,571 --> 00:05:02,573
[upbeat music continues]

81
00:05:29,308 --> 00:05:31,310
[people screaming excitedly]

82
00:05:36,940 --> 00:05:38,942
[screaming continues]

83
00:05:40,027 --> 00:05:41,528
[Rose] What's up?

84
00:05:41,612 --> 00:05:45,657
-Great timing. Come on now. Quickly.
-[Rose] What? Why are we…?

85
00:05:45,741 --> 00:05:48,494
-Move, move.
-What is going on here? Hey! Hey!

86
00:05:48,577 --> 00:05:50,621
-[upbeat music continues]
-[screaming continues]

87
00:05:50,704 --> 00:05:55,000
-Oh my… oh my God!
-[screaming]

88
00:05:55,084 --> 00:05:57,711
What's happening? I can't see a thing.

89
00:05:57,795 --> 00:05:59,296
What do they look like?

90
00:05:59,380 --> 00:06:01,048
Just like Jack. Mm.

91
00:06:01,131 --> 00:06:02,591
-[girl 2] So true.
-Who's Jack?

92
00:06:02,674 --> 00:06:03,926
The one in the Titanic.

93
00:06:04,009 --> 00:06:06,303
-Leonardo DiCaprio?
-Sure, babe.

94
00:06:06,387 --> 00:06:08,847
-You know, I got a crush on that guy.
-Me too.

95
00:06:08,931 --> 00:06:12,101
-Look, he's coming out.
-[boy] Oh my God!

96
00:06:12,184 --> 00:06:13,852
-[screaming continues]
-Oh! Ugh!

97
00:06:13,936 --> 00:06:15,437
[excited clamoring]

98
00:06:15,521 --> 00:06:18,440
-[screaming continues]
-[woman screams]

99
00:06:18,524 --> 00:06:20,442
[upbeat music playing]

100
00:06:21,402 --> 00:06:25,364
-Oh! Hey! Hey, stop shouting. Stop!
-[screaming continues]

101
00:06:25,447 --> 00:06:27,408
-Don't yell at Ms. Melai.
-[Ms. Melai screams]

102
00:06:27,491 --> 00:06:28,742
-Ms. Melai…
-[screams]

103
00:06:28,826 --> 00:06:31,829
-Hey, don't shout! Stop shouting!
-Go away!

104
00:06:31,912 --> 00:06:34,456
-Ms. Melai, let's, um…
-What's happening?

105
00:06:34,540 --> 00:06:37,709
[shakily] Have we had another
stabbing incident with a ballpoint?!

106
00:06:37,793 --> 00:06:39,545
-Uh, no. Ms. Melai, it's more.
-Oh!

107
00:06:40,129 --> 00:06:42,673
-You know the guy from the Titanic?
-What?

108
00:06:42,756 --> 00:06:44,007
Leonardo DiCapri?

109
00:06:44,925 --> 00:06:46,802
-Caprio. Caprio.
-Caprio? Oh!

110
00:06:46,885 --> 00:06:49,847
-Ms. Melai.
-Caprio, Caprio. Uh!

111
00:06:49,930 --> 00:06:52,099
-Come to the garden. Let's go.
-Okay!

112
00:06:52,182 --> 00:06:53,684
-[girl 3] He's coming!
-Let's go…

113
00:06:53,767 --> 00:06:56,311
-Oh my God!
-[boy] No, no…

114
00:06:56,812 --> 00:07:00,149
-Oh my God!
-[all screaming]

115
00:07:01,859 --> 00:07:03,026
What's your problem?

116
00:07:03,110 --> 00:07:07,156
-You're my problem now.
-[screaming resumes]

117
00:07:07,239 --> 00:07:11,702
[yelps] He's holding my hand.
I think I'm in love.

118
00:07:11,785 --> 00:07:13,787
[all screaming]

119
00:07:16,206 --> 00:07:18,208
[screaming continues]

120
00:07:19,793 --> 00:07:21,211
[music stops]

121
00:07:21,295 --> 00:07:25,507
[Rose] There you are! Camellia and Dahlia,
I've put you two together,

122
00:07:25,591 --> 00:07:29,386
so that when you finally bloom,
you'll be so beautiful, okay?

123
00:07:29,470 --> 00:07:32,973
I've also replaced your soil. [laughs]
Okay, that's it.

124
00:07:33,474 --> 00:07:36,185
[Ms. Melai] Stop it.
They'll start talking back soon.

125
00:07:36,268 --> 00:07:40,564
[laughs] My mother always said
to treat them like they were my own kids.

126
00:07:40,647 --> 00:07:44,985
-[Ms. Melai] Mm!
-Talk to them and also, take care. Eh?

127
00:07:45,068 --> 00:07:46,987
Do you have a lot of plants
at home as well?

128
00:07:47,070 --> 00:07:50,532
Oh, of course.
Especially when Mom was still here.

129
00:07:50,616 --> 00:07:52,951
She was always planting
and growing things, you see.

130
00:07:53,035 --> 00:07:57,122
-So, you take after her?
-Oh yeah, I got her good looks as well!

131
00:07:59,917 --> 00:08:04,838
Ugh! No! Oh, my amnesia.
And I forgot the fertilizer.

132
00:08:04,922 --> 00:08:06,423
I should have brought it down.

133
00:08:06,507 --> 00:08:08,050
-It's behind the tree.
-Ms. Melai.

134
00:08:08,133 --> 00:08:09,426
-I'll go get it.
-Really?

135
00:08:09,510 --> 00:08:10,969
-Calm down now.
-That'd be great.

136
00:08:11,053 --> 00:08:14,056
It's… it's right there
in the jute sack. It's just there…

137
00:08:14,139 --> 00:08:16,934
-Uh, I'll deal with it.
-Thank you. Thank you so much!

138
00:08:17,017 --> 00:08:17,893
[blows raspberry]

139
00:08:17,976 --> 00:08:19,978
[indistinct chatter]

140
00:08:26,944 --> 00:08:30,072
Excuse me.
This is the computer room, right?

141
00:08:30,155 --> 00:08:32,533
-Yes.
-Can I use them?

142
00:08:33,033 --> 00:08:34,409
No, they're broken.

143
00:08:34,493 --> 00:08:36,036
Uh… All of them?

144
00:08:38,413 --> 00:08:39,498
That's not…

145
00:08:40,666 --> 00:08:41,542
[sighs]

146
00:08:42,960 --> 00:08:45,170
[poignant music playing]

147
00:08:49,091 --> 00:08:50,509
[dramatic note plays]

148
00:08:50,592 --> 00:08:54,012
[all] Hi, Jordan! [screaming]

149
00:08:54,096 --> 00:08:55,389
Jesus.

150
00:08:57,182 --> 00:08:59,351
[upbeat music playing]

151
00:09:01,603 --> 00:09:03,438
Move. Get out of the way.

152
00:09:04,439 --> 00:09:05,732
[growl]

153
00:09:08,569 --> 00:09:10,112
[growl]

154
00:09:13,824 --> 00:09:14,866
Damn!

155
00:09:16,159 --> 00:09:18,078
-[music builds]
-[screaming]

156
00:09:26,503 --> 00:09:28,463
-[screaming in distance]
-[indistinct]

157
00:09:29,715 --> 00:09:31,633
Stop it. Please!

158
00:09:34,094 --> 00:09:35,804
Later. Yeah.

159
00:09:37,389 --> 00:09:40,434
Jordan, Jordan. Jordan, where are you?

160
00:09:41,351 --> 00:09:43,353
Girl, where is he?

161
00:09:43,437 --> 00:09:45,230
-You go down that way.
-Okay.

162
00:09:45,314 --> 00:09:46,732
And you guys go to the right.

163
00:09:46,815 --> 00:09:49,860
-Should we use a secret code?
-Well, screaming is good.

164
00:09:49,943 --> 00:09:51,153
And you'll be where?

165
00:09:51,236 --> 00:09:52,654
-Yeah.
-Just here.

166
00:09:52,738 --> 00:09:55,240
-You think? Come on.
-Okay, let's go.

167
00:09:55,324 --> 00:09:56,825
-[screaming]
-[all] Jordan!

168
00:09:56,908 --> 00:09:59,328
-Uh. Later. See ya!
-Later.

169
00:10:03,081 --> 00:10:05,500
-[music fades]
-Damn it. Wow!

170
00:10:05,584 --> 00:10:07,336
[screaming continues in distance]

171
00:10:07,419 --> 00:10:10,088
[upbeat music resumes]

172
00:10:32,944 --> 00:10:35,113
Ugh. Smells. [sniffs]

173
00:10:35,822 --> 00:10:37,574
Oh, man. [panting]

174
00:10:39,284 --> 00:10:40,535
[music builds]

175
00:10:40,619 --> 00:10:41,495
[Rose] Hey!

176
00:10:42,746 --> 00:10:44,206
[music continues]

177
00:11:04,810 --> 00:11:06,019
-[music stops]
-[Jordan grunts]

178
00:11:06,770 --> 00:11:08,480
[gasps, groans]

179
00:11:09,231 --> 00:11:12,234
What? Oh my God! Shit!

180
00:11:12,859 --> 00:11:13,860
Are you…?

181
00:11:14,903 --> 00:11:16,822
-Gee.
-What is that?

182
00:11:17,698 --> 00:11:20,450
[gags] What's that smell?

183
00:11:22,077 --> 00:11:22,911
Shit?

184
00:11:23,495 --> 00:11:26,248
Are you serious?
Why are you walking around with shit?

185
00:11:26,331 --> 00:11:27,582
That's fertilizer.

186
00:11:28,542 --> 00:11:30,961
That's for… That's for my…

187
00:11:31,837 --> 00:11:33,422
-That's for my…
-For your what now, huh?

188
00:11:34,756 --> 00:11:38,176
For my scholarship.
You know, community service.

189
00:11:39,094 --> 00:11:40,053
So full of it.

190
00:11:40,137 --> 00:11:43,640
[scoffs] Scholarship.
That is not fertilizer. This is shit.

191
00:11:44,349 --> 00:11:47,894
You keep saying shit.
You're shit. It's fertilizer.

192
00:11:47,978 --> 00:11:49,813
You think you're so great
but you're a jerk.

193
00:11:49,896 --> 00:11:51,523
You bumped into me anyway.

194
00:11:51,606 --> 00:11:53,567
-So it's my fault we both smell like shit?
-Uh…

195
00:11:53,650 --> 00:11:55,944
-Yeah! Duh!
-You shouldn't have brought this.

196
00:11:56,027 --> 00:11:58,989
-Duh!
-Don't be arrogant. I know everyone here.

197
00:11:59,072 --> 00:12:00,907
If you wanna go for it,
I'll snap my fingers,

198
00:12:00,991 --> 00:12:02,617
and they'll be waiting at the front gate.

199
00:12:02,701 --> 00:12:04,202
If that's what you're after…

200
00:12:04,286 --> 00:12:06,455
-Slow. Stop. Stop.
-My fingers snap and you're dead.

201
00:12:06,538 --> 00:12:08,039
-I can't even understand you…
-Uh…

202
00:12:08,123 --> 00:12:09,499
-Just say sorry…
-Speak clearly.

203
00:12:09,583 --> 00:12:11,543
-Say sorry to me now.
-[screaming]

204
00:12:11,626 --> 00:12:14,212
-You say sorry now.
-You want me to say sorry?

205
00:12:15,130 --> 00:12:18,175
-[Jordan, frustrated] Oh my God!
-[screaming continues]

206
00:12:18,258 --> 00:12:20,260
-What's going on?
-I don't know…

207
00:12:20,343 --> 00:12:23,513
-[Jordan] It's your fault.
-Don't be so rude! You son of a…

208
00:12:25,098 --> 00:12:29,019
-Hey, are you from around here?
-He's not listening to you.

209
00:12:29,102 --> 00:12:32,647
-[keyboard clacking]
-[sniffs] Foreigners don't wash often.

210
00:12:33,398 --> 00:12:36,401
-[boy 3] That's… That's body odor, right?
-No way.

211
00:12:36,485 --> 00:12:37,444
[sniffs] Ugh!

212
00:12:37,527 --> 00:12:39,404
-It's shit.
-Holy shit!

213
00:12:39,488 --> 00:12:41,031
-Horrible!
-Smell like shit, huh?

214
00:12:41,114 --> 00:12:42,073
-[boy 3] Uh-oh.
-Oh.

215
00:12:42,574 --> 00:12:43,825
Come on, huh?

216
00:12:44,326 --> 00:12:46,953
What, you thought I didn't understand?
Thought I didn't understand?

217
00:12:47,037 --> 00:12:49,623
-Come on, come on! Say it to my face.
-[boy 1] Sorry.

218
00:12:49,706 --> 00:12:52,501
-What? How is it you're still here?
-[boy 2] Rose, he's bullying us.

219
00:12:54,211 --> 00:12:58,089
-So, what are you doing here?
-This girl's the reason I smell like shit.

220
00:12:58,173 --> 00:12:59,049
Shit girl.

221
00:12:59,132 --> 00:13:03,303
-Who are you calling "shit girl," huh?
-You got shat on too? You smell like shit.

222
00:13:03,386 --> 00:13:06,389
Hey, that's not it.
He ran into me. I had fertilizer.

223
00:13:06,473 --> 00:13:09,810
I dropped all the fertilizer.
I'd say that's his fault, is it not?

224
00:13:09,893 --> 00:13:11,686
-Just tell them the truth.
-Oh, what truth?

225
00:13:11,770 --> 00:13:14,439
You're just like everyone at that school.
Chasing me, following me…

226
00:13:14,523 --> 00:13:18,151
Enough! Seriously, can't even
get an ounce of peace and quiet.

227
00:13:18,235 --> 00:13:21,863
Oh, for someone who's so high and mighty,
there's a lot you should learn.

228
00:13:21,947 --> 00:13:23,240
This is where I work.

229
00:13:23,323 --> 00:13:26,660
Before you were even here,
I work here, you colonizer.

230
00:13:26,743 --> 00:13:29,913
-[boys and Rose] Oh! Colonizer!
-Colonizer?

231
00:13:29,996 --> 00:13:32,165
-Colonizer? What the fuck?
-Hey.

232
00:13:32,249 --> 00:13:35,168
-[Jordan] Colonizer?
-No swearing in here, no more swearing.

233
00:13:35,252 --> 00:13:36,962
You can't swear in here, so get lost.

234
00:13:37,045 --> 00:13:39,089
-I'm not leaving.
-"I'm not leaving." Get out!

235
00:13:39,172 --> 00:13:41,049
I paid for the hour,
so I'm finishing my hour.

236
00:13:41,132 --> 00:13:44,469
Think you're a tough guy, do you?
Okay, that's it. This is gonna cost you.

237
00:13:44,553 --> 00:13:46,930
You can't do that.
I'm a paying customer. Come on.

238
00:13:47,430 --> 00:13:48,390
-What the hell?
-Go on.

239
00:13:48,473 --> 00:13:51,434
Oh, big man crying over ten pesos.

240
00:13:51,518 --> 00:13:54,062
Here's ten pesos.
I don't need your ten pesos.

241
00:13:54,145 --> 00:13:55,730
-Get out.
-[boy 2] Go home, go on.

242
00:13:55,814 --> 00:13:58,316
Where's your boss?
I'll talk to him right now.

243
00:13:58,400 --> 00:13:59,776
-He wants the boss now?
-Boss?

244
00:13:59,860 --> 00:14:01,152
-He wants the boss.
-Boss.

245
00:14:01,236 --> 00:14:04,531
-Actually, I'm my own boss. I'm the boss!
-[boy 1] Oh! Yeah!

246
00:14:04,614 --> 00:14:07,576
-[Rose] And that's that. So get out. Okay?
-[boy 2] Go! Go home!

247
00:14:07,659 --> 00:14:09,119
-[boy 3] What an asshole.
-You stink.

248
00:14:09,202 --> 00:14:10,537
[overlapping chatter]

249
00:14:10,620 --> 00:14:13,039
Even the other customers think you smell.

250
00:14:13,123 --> 00:14:15,792
-Can you smell yourself? I know you can…
-It's you. Just leave.

251
00:14:15,876 --> 00:14:19,045
-I know you can smell yourself.
-It's you. You stink… like shit.

252
00:14:19,129 --> 00:14:21,214
-See you. Stinky.
-Like shit!

253
00:14:21,882 --> 00:14:23,258
[boy 3] Uh, gross.

254
00:14:24,885 --> 00:14:26,094
[music stops]

255
00:14:31,141 --> 00:14:33,852
I don't want to be here.
I don't want to be here.

256
00:14:35,103 --> 00:14:36,104
[grunts]

257
00:14:38,148 --> 00:14:41,693
Why am I here? Why am I here?
Why am I here, Mom? Why?

258
00:15:03,840 --> 00:15:06,760
[melancholic music playing]

259
00:15:25,195 --> 00:15:26,988
-[Jordan] Mom.
-What?

260
00:15:27,656 --> 00:15:30,617
-Can I have cereal?
-Huh?

261
00:15:30,700 --> 00:15:34,454
Oh, no, we don't have any cereal.
I haven't got to the store yet.

262
00:15:34,537 --> 00:15:36,790
Uh, there's only dried fish.

263
00:15:36,873 --> 00:15:38,416
-Thank you so much.
-Thank you.

264
00:15:38,500 --> 00:15:41,169
Mom, you know
I don't eat rice in the morning.

265
00:15:41,252 --> 00:15:42,879
Oh? And why is that?

266
00:15:44,130 --> 00:15:48,551
Mom, we've gone over this so many times.
Dad never ate rice. Americans don't.

267
00:15:48,635 --> 00:15:52,305
Oh. But you're also Pinoy,
so eat your rice.

268
00:15:52,389 --> 00:15:56,476
-No, I'm American.
-[sighs] You know what, Jordan?

269
00:15:56,559 --> 00:15:59,813
If you keep acting like this,
how will you ever adjust?

270
00:16:00,647 --> 00:16:03,900
You need to be more open,
or you'll never make new friends.

271
00:16:07,278 --> 00:16:08,989
Mom, can't I just be with Dad?

272
00:16:09,864 --> 00:16:11,074
[sighs]

273
00:16:12,909 --> 00:16:14,369
Mom. Mom, fine.

274
00:16:14,452 --> 00:16:16,830
Can… Can you please
just buy me a computer?

275
00:16:18,289 --> 00:16:21,376
-What for?
-So I can email Dad.

276
00:16:22,043 --> 00:16:23,503
He can get me out of here.

277
00:16:24,921 --> 00:16:26,172
Has he replied?

278
00:16:28,717 --> 00:16:30,260
When he writes back.

279
00:16:31,094 --> 00:16:32,971
So, keep emailing him.

280
00:16:33,054 --> 00:16:35,682
Mom, how can I keep emailing him
if we don't have a computer?

281
00:16:35,765 --> 00:16:39,144
Please stop it, okay?
You'll be late for school.

282
00:16:39,227 --> 00:16:40,687
Come on. Please, huh?

283
00:16:42,439 --> 00:16:44,441
[melancholic music continues]

284
00:16:47,527 --> 00:16:48,611
Jordan.

285
00:16:50,196 --> 00:16:52,365
-Your lunch. Jordan!
-[loud music playing on headphones]

286
00:16:55,618 --> 00:16:57,620
[music fades in the distance]

287
00:16:58,204 --> 00:17:00,457
[indistinct chatter]

288
00:17:09,966 --> 00:17:13,762
Hey! Would you be able
to help me get the chocolate drink?

289
00:17:13,845 --> 00:17:15,805
I can't reach that high.

290
00:17:17,682 --> 00:17:19,976
Hey, that drink's mine! Give it here.

291
00:17:20,060 --> 00:17:22,062
What do you mean it's yours?
I'm already holding it.

292
00:17:22,145 --> 00:17:23,104
Give it here.

293
00:17:23,188 --> 00:17:26,107
I asked the shopkeeper for it
and that's why I hadn't already bought it.

294
00:17:26,691 --> 00:17:28,860
-Let me have that.
-It's not my fault you're small.

295
00:17:28,943 --> 00:17:30,195
Bully.

296
00:17:31,196 --> 00:17:32,655
Think you're a model?

297
00:17:32,739 --> 00:17:35,784
I think… Why would you say that?
Think I'm a model…

298
00:17:35,867 --> 00:17:38,119
That's all you guys care about
in this place.

299
00:17:38,745 --> 00:17:41,164
-Fucking looks.
-You…

300
00:17:41,873 --> 00:17:45,043
You know, "fuck." You know "shit."
Do you know more words than that?

301
00:17:45,543 --> 00:17:48,046
Where were your parents
when you were learning to talk?

302
00:17:51,174 --> 00:17:53,218
[somber music playing]

303
00:17:55,011 --> 00:17:56,304
I should have that!

304
00:17:56,387 --> 00:17:58,473
[energetic rock music playing]

305
00:17:58,556 --> 00:18:00,350
[slurps loudly]

306
00:18:09,275 --> 00:18:10,693
Now it's wasted.

307
00:18:12,612 --> 00:18:14,614
[rock music fades]

308
00:18:14,697 --> 00:18:16,533
[indistinct chatter]

309
00:18:16,616 --> 00:18:17,992
Okay.

310
00:18:20,203 --> 00:18:21,246
Hey.

311
00:18:21,830 --> 00:18:23,748
-One hour.
-Oh!

312
00:18:25,834 --> 00:18:28,962
There's no available computers
for you today.

313
00:18:30,088 --> 00:18:32,549
There's a computer right there.
I'm not blind.

314
00:18:32,632 --> 00:18:36,427
Not that one.
Because that one cannot be hired.

315
00:18:36,511 --> 00:18:39,013
Someone's using it. Too bad for you.

316
00:18:41,891 --> 00:18:45,520
-Fine. I'll wait.
-Okay. You wait.

317
00:18:45,603 --> 00:18:47,147
-I will.
-Good for you.

318
00:18:47,647 --> 00:18:50,316
Okay. [scoffs] "I'll wait."

319
00:18:50,900 --> 00:18:53,486
-Rose!
-Ah, Ms. Berta!

320
00:18:53,570 --> 00:18:56,406
-You know why I'm here. I need an hour.
-Of course, Ms. Berta.

321
00:18:56,489 --> 00:18:58,533
-That one's yours!
-Yes, my favorite.

322
00:18:58,616 --> 00:19:00,785
-Thank you!
-Hey, okay! Have fun, Ms. Berta.

323
00:19:00,869 --> 00:19:02,912
Hey. Hey!

324
00:19:03,413 --> 00:19:06,291
That's mine. I waited.
You told me to wait. I waited.

325
00:19:06,374 --> 00:19:09,794
She's a regular
and she made a reservation. Did you?

326
00:19:09,878 --> 00:19:11,129
-No reservation, huh?
-Reserve?

327
00:19:11,212 --> 00:19:13,882
I heard the whole conversation back there.
She did not reserve.

328
00:19:13,965 --> 00:19:16,885
You want me to tell the barangay, huh?
I'll tell the barangay right now.

329
00:19:16,968 --> 00:19:18,928
-Tell what?
-I'll tell the barangay right now.

330
00:19:19,012 --> 00:19:20,471
And I'll have them close up the shop.

331
00:19:20,555 --> 00:19:22,765
-Oh, where are you going?
-The barangay, you heard me.

332
00:19:22,849 --> 00:19:25,894
[mockingly] Oh, barungey, okay.
Let's make a trip to the barungey.

333
00:19:25,977 --> 00:19:29,314
And I'll report you to the barungey
'cause you stole my drink, didn't you?

334
00:19:29,397 --> 00:19:31,691
-Huh? Remember, huh?
-One drink. One chocolate drink.

335
00:19:31,774 --> 00:19:34,194
And you're not gonna
let me use your fricking computer?

336
00:19:34,277 --> 00:19:36,613
-That's it. Okay, fine, I'll buy you ten.
-Uh-huh.

337
00:19:36,696 --> 00:19:38,156
-You want ten?
-It's not about that.

338
00:19:38,239 --> 00:19:39,908
-It's not about that.
-What?

339
00:19:39,991 --> 00:19:42,327
-It's about my, um…
-What?

340
00:19:42,410 --> 00:19:43,453
My…

341
00:19:44,287 --> 00:19:45,246
principles.

342
00:19:45,330 --> 00:19:48,583
[scoffs] Principles?
What are you talking about, principles?

343
00:19:48,666 --> 00:19:49,959
That's none of your business.

344
00:19:50,043 --> 00:19:52,503
-You're making fun of me? You wanna…?
-There, you see that?

345
00:19:52,587 --> 00:19:54,797
You'll be beaten up if you don't leave.

346
00:19:54,881 --> 00:19:57,926
Yeah, that's right, you'll be beaten up
if you don't leave right now.

347
00:19:58,009 --> 00:19:59,135
-Oh!
-[Rose] Is that clear?

348
00:19:59,219 --> 00:20:00,678
Oh my God, just go away.

349
00:20:01,262 --> 00:20:04,474
Oh. Oh, I feel sorry for you. Just go.

350
00:20:04,557 --> 00:20:05,683
-[Jordan grunts]
-Oh!

351
00:20:05,767 --> 00:20:08,269
I'll beat you up, boy. Small little boy.

352
00:20:08,353 --> 00:20:10,855
[energetic rock music playing]

353
00:20:35,171 --> 00:20:36,714
[music continues]

354
00:21:13,376 --> 00:21:15,169
[music stops]

355
00:21:15,253 --> 00:21:17,505
Hey! Why are you all wet?

356
00:21:18,965 --> 00:21:20,925
'Cause of some stupid girl.

357
00:21:21,009 --> 00:21:23,219
You pick fights with girls now?

358
00:21:24,595 --> 00:21:28,016
-Jordan, that's not right.
-Come on, of course I know that.

359
00:21:28,099 --> 00:21:30,101
She picks fights with me.

360
00:21:31,394 --> 00:21:34,355
She doesn't let me go
in the computer shop or use the computer.

361
00:21:34,439 --> 00:21:37,275
Do you want me
to talk to whoever's in charge?

362
00:21:37,817 --> 00:21:42,572
-Aunt Kakai knows the owner.
-No, I'm fine. I can handle it myself.

363
00:21:43,740 --> 00:21:45,158
-Okay.
-I'm fine.

364
00:21:47,952 --> 00:21:50,079
But, you know,
there's still a way that you can help,

365
00:21:50,163 --> 00:21:51,456
if you really want to, Mom.

366
00:21:51,539 --> 00:21:54,459
-Mmm?
-I've been asking about it all week.

367
00:21:55,001 --> 00:21:58,838
Come on, Mom, can we please
just get a computer, that's all I need.

368
00:21:58,921 --> 00:22:02,300
I'm sorry, son,
but it's just not in our budget.

369
00:22:02,383 --> 00:22:06,220
I'm still new at the resort,
and hey, we have to save our money

370
00:22:06,304 --> 00:22:07,680
for all the things we really need.

371
00:22:08,264 --> 00:22:11,184
But Mom, I… I need it,
so I can message Dad.

372
00:22:11,267 --> 00:22:14,354
-Has he emailed back?
-Why keep asking me if he's answered?

373
00:22:14,437 --> 00:22:16,606
How am I supposed
to know if he's answered? I don't--

374
00:22:16,689 --> 00:22:20,234
Your father hasn't replied,
and it's been ten years or more.

375
00:22:20,318 --> 00:22:22,653
-Maybe it's time to give up.
-No.

376
00:22:23,237 --> 00:22:26,115
I will not give up on my dad.
I will not do what you did.

377
00:22:26,199 --> 00:22:28,201
[melancholic music playing]

378
00:22:31,621 --> 00:22:34,999
I… Mom, he's going to answer me.

379
00:22:35,875 --> 00:22:38,878
I know he will.
He will, because I am his son.

380
00:22:42,131 --> 00:22:43,716
He's gonna answer me.

381
00:23:02,944 --> 00:23:03,820
I know.

382
00:23:04,404 --> 00:23:07,448
No computers available
even though you're just opening up shop.

383
00:23:07,949 --> 00:23:08,950
Yeah.

384
00:23:09,784 --> 00:23:12,370
No available computers for you.

385
00:23:14,580 --> 00:23:15,623
I'll wait.

386
00:23:22,213 --> 00:23:23,881
Even if I have to wait all day.

387
00:23:29,220 --> 00:23:30,263
Then, wait.

388
00:23:31,431 --> 00:23:33,433
[melancholic guitar music playing]

389
00:23:34,809 --> 00:23:37,395
-Ah, Ms. Berta!
-Hi, Rose.

390
00:23:37,895 --> 00:23:38,896
Baby time.

391
00:23:39,397 --> 00:23:42,150
Wow! Looks like you're moving
to the next stage.

392
00:23:42,233 --> 00:23:43,609
-You look good together.
-You think?

393
00:23:43,693 --> 00:23:45,653
-Really good, Ms. Berta!
-Thank you!

394
00:23:45,736 --> 00:23:47,738
-[computer game SFX]
-[Berta] She said we're a match.

395
00:23:47,822 --> 00:23:50,491
Uh… I need you to finish up.

396
00:23:50,575 --> 00:23:53,494
-Thirty minutes more.
-Okay, thirty minutes. You as well.

397
00:23:53,578 --> 00:23:56,622
-No, wait. I'm just finishing up.
-Come on. Really?

398
00:23:57,623 --> 00:23:58,666
Rose.

399
00:23:59,709 --> 00:24:01,627
He's been here since this morning.

400
00:24:04,964 --> 00:24:07,758
He said he'd wait,
that it didn't matter how long it took.

401
00:24:07,842 --> 00:24:09,260
It's a long time.

402
00:24:09,844 --> 00:24:11,554
See how long he lasts.

403
00:24:13,014 --> 00:24:14,640
-Many thanks!
-They're all done.

404
00:24:14,724 --> 00:24:15,933
Thank you.

405
00:24:16,767 --> 00:24:18,769
[music continues]

406
00:24:48,299 --> 00:24:49,884
[music fades]

407
00:24:49,967 --> 00:24:53,930
Hey, Rose. Maybe it's important
what Mr. USA needs to do.

408
00:24:54,013 --> 00:24:55,932
He's been waiting out there all day.

409
00:24:59,393 --> 00:25:03,314
Come on, Rose.
Have some mercy. Poor thing.

410
00:25:07,193 --> 00:25:08,819
Show some heart, Rose.

411
00:25:13,491 --> 00:25:16,452
Uh, you three.
You changed your minds quickly.

412
00:25:34,178 --> 00:25:35,388
Psst. Hey.

413
00:25:39,684 --> 00:25:41,811
We're closing in 15 minutes.

414
00:25:41,894 --> 00:25:43,396
Well, I'm not leaving.

415
00:25:44,605 --> 00:25:46,023
Not until I've read my email.

416
00:25:46,524 --> 00:25:50,903
I'll fix the Xerox machine.
I'll be there for five minutes.

417
00:25:54,448 --> 00:25:55,575
What do I care?

418
00:25:57,535 --> 00:26:00,705
I said, I'll be there for five minutes.

419
00:26:05,126 --> 00:26:06,127
Dude, use this.

420
00:26:06,210 --> 00:26:08,963
-Wait, wait.
-It's free. Sit down there.

421
00:26:09,505 --> 00:26:10,673
Come on, go.

422
00:26:13,342 --> 00:26:16,971
-[upbeat music playing]
-[machine rattling]

423
00:26:24,353 --> 00:26:25,563
Come on.

424
00:26:37,658 --> 00:26:39,660
[music turns melancholic]

425
00:26:53,716 --> 00:26:57,762
Whoa! That was quick.
Less than five minutes, huh?

426
00:26:58,304 --> 00:27:01,265
-Is he done?
-Weird. He left so quickly.

427
00:27:05,686 --> 00:27:06,771
Are you okay?

428
00:27:07,647 --> 00:27:11,984
I just got a bit weirded out
by that customer from America, Dad.

429
00:27:12,860 --> 00:27:13,861
[father] Mm.

430
00:27:15,279 --> 00:27:16,530
Tess's son.

431
00:27:17,657 --> 00:27:18,616
Handsome boy, huh?

432
00:27:19,325 --> 00:27:20,242
Hm?

433
00:27:20,868 --> 00:27:22,995
-No.
-Mm? You think he's cute.

434
00:27:23,079 --> 00:27:26,248
-You do! Look, your nostrils are flaring.
-No. No, no.

435
00:27:26,332 --> 00:27:29,210
-Oh, come on. They're not. You're silly.
-[father laughs]

436
00:27:29,293 --> 00:27:30,836
-Gotcha!
-Hey. Hey, no.

437
00:27:30,920 --> 00:27:32,004
-Because Dad…
-Mm.

438
00:27:32,088 --> 00:27:34,924
He keeps on pestering me
to get into Green Skies.

439
00:27:35,007 --> 00:27:37,218
-Mmm.
-That's the truth.

440
00:27:37,301 --> 00:27:40,805
But when he logs on,
all he does is check emails.

441
00:27:40,888 --> 00:27:44,892
He doesn't do Friendster
or games or open YM.

442
00:27:44,975 --> 00:27:47,812
That goes to show
he doesn't think those things matter.

443
00:27:48,312 --> 00:27:53,526
Also… Maybe the thing that matters
is who's getting that email.

444
00:27:53,609 --> 00:27:54,777
Could be his father.

445
00:27:55,403 --> 00:28:00,116
You know? It can be really hard
being far away from those you love.

446
00:28:00,199 --> 00:28:02,201
[melancholic music playing]

447
00:28:04,578 --> 00:28:07,289
A bit like Mom and you, hey?

448
00:28:07,373 --> 00:28:10,876
Hm? No. Your mom and I are different.

449
00:28:12,128 --> 00:28:15,965
I know that she'll be back here.
I know at some point she'll come home.

450
00:28:16,716 --> 00:28:19,677
But Jordan's dad? Who knows?

451
00:28:21,053 --> 00:28:23,931
So, try to be a bit more sympathetic.

452
00:28:24,807 --> 00:28:26,809
[melancholic music continues]

453
00:28:32,481 --> 00:28:33,524
Uh!

454
00:28:34,358 --> 00:28:37,236
Uh! Head back, head back.
I'll get some ice.

455
00:28:37,737 --> 00:28:39,530
How come your nose is bleeding again?

456
00:28:40,114 --> 00:28:43,617
Maybe I'm allergic
to being kind, Dad! [laughs]

457
00:28:43,701 --> 00:28:45,411
[father] Head back. Head back. Head back.

458
00:28:45,494 --> 00:28:48,122
-Head back! Where's… Where's that towel?
-[laughing]

459
00:28:48,205 --> 00:28:51,292
[energetic rock music playing in distance]

460
00:28:54,670 --> 00:28:56,630
-Rose, Rose.
-Oh, look, here comes Rose. Sit here.

461
00:28:56,714 --> 00:28:58,257
[girl] Come sit here.

462
00:28:59,341 --> 00:29:00,843
[indistinct chatter]

463
00:29:00,926 --> 00:29:01,969
Hello?

464
00:29:02,052 --> 00:29:04,805
[energetic rock music
playing through headphones]

465
00:29:09,226 --> 00:29:11,353
Hello! Hi!

466
00:29:12,313 --> 00:29:13,814
[volume increases]

467
00:29:21,572 --> 00:29:23,574
[singing along with music on CD player]

468
00:29:35,294 --> 00:29:36,462
Oh! Yeah.

469
00:29:38,130 --> 00:29:40,132
[continues singing along with music]

470
00:29:49,809 --> 00:29:52,895
[both sing along with music on CD player]

471
00:30:03,072 --> 00:30:04,281
[Rose] Let's go!

472
00:30:04,949 --> 00:30:06,951
[sings in menacing voice]

473
00:30:15,417 --> 00:30:16,919
-[voice rises and stops]
-[song ends]

474
00:30:17,878 --> 00:30:19,213
[applause breaks out]

475
00:30:19,296 --> 00:30:23,843
Thank you! Thank you!
Thank you! And thank you!

476
00:30:24,635 --> 00:30:26,887
-[cheering]
-Thank you! [laughs]

477
00:30:27,555 --> 00:30:30,140
-You're awesome. Are you in a band?
-[music stops]

478
00:30:33,519 --> 00:30:37,398
What? Being a singer, worth a try.

479
00:30:39,316 --> 00:30:43,404
I… just listen to their music. That's it.

480
00:30:45,197 --> 00:30:48,158
Interesting you can
sing a song in Tagalog.

481
00:30:48,242 --> 00:30:50,619
I thought English
was your only language. [laughs]

482
00:30:51,871 --> 00:30:54,957
So what if it's Tagalog?
I like their music.

483
00:30:55,791 --> 00:30:58,627
Lots of people ask me
to burn GSK CDs at the shop.

484
00:30:58,711 --> 00:31:00,588
So, I've memorized some of the songs.

485
00:31:00,671 --> 00:31:04,008
But if I ever play them at the shop,
Dad will always blast me.

486
00:31:04,091 --> 00:31:07,136
-I get killed! [laughs]
-[laughs] Me too!

487
00:31:07,219 --> 00:31:08,512
-My mom…
-Yeah?

488
00:31:08,596 --> 00:31:11,974
My mom is the same, she doesn't like it.
Maybe it's an old people thing?

489
00:31:12,057 --> 00:31:13,475
[both laugh]

490
00:31:13,976 --> 00:31:17,396
Huh. You know, my dad…
My dad, though, he likes this music.

491
00:31:18,063 --> 00:31:21,442
He's really into heavy metal.
He likes GSK.

492
00:31:26,780 --> 00:31:28,782
[whimsical music playing]

493
00:31:32,828 --> 00:31:34,079
What's this?

494
00:31:35,080 --> 00:31:36,749
-What?
-What are you doing?

495
00:31:36,832 --> 00:31:38,709
Why are you acting all nice, huh?

496
00:31:38,792 --> 00:31:41,629
Because you're by yourself,
I thought I'd sit with you.

497
00:31:42,129 --> 00:31:44,173
I felt sorry for you.

498
00:31:44,256 --> 00:31:46,800
I don't want your pity. I'm fine.

499
00:31:48,177 --> 00:31:50,346
There, there, it's okay.

500
00:31:51,305 --> 00:31:54,850
Oh. There, there. Really?

501
00:31:55,351 --> 00:31:58,562
"There, there." That's four! Want this?

502
00:31:59,855 --> 00:32:00,898
I'm fine.

503
00:32:10,991 --> 00:32:12,576
[screams]

504
00:32:12,660 --> 00:32:14,912
-Jordan, hi.
-Hi. Hi.

505
00:32:14,995 --> 00:32:16,038
[Rose] Jordan!

506
00:32:18,958 --> 00:32:22,252
-Are you going to Green Skies?
-[boy and girl] Bye. Bye.

507
00:32:22,836 --> 00:32:23,796
Maybe.

508
00:32:24,296 --> 00:32:26,173
Maybe? Just say if you are.

509
00:32:28,133 --> 00:32:30,177
Look, why are you
being so nice to me, man?

510
00:32:30,260 --> 00:32:33,722
I don't get it.
Don't be sorry for me. I'm fine.

511
00:32:33,806 --> 00:32:36,183
You're joking. You're a drama queen.

512
00:32:37,267 --> 00:32:41,146
-Actually, I want to say sorry.
-Sorry for what?

513
00:32:42,773 --> 00:32:45,109
I'm sorry for not being nice.

514
00:32:45,609 --> 00:32:49,029
Which you already know
because I'm apologizing now.

515
00:32:49,113 --> 00:32:50,447
-I won't grovel.
-[laughs]

516
00:32:50,531 --> 00:32:54,451
You can go to Green Skies.
You can email all you want.

517
00:32:57,454 --> 00:32:59,999
[tender music playing]

518
00:33:01,542 --> 00:33:05,921
Mm… My mom lives away for work.

519
00:33:06,922 --> 00:33:12,011
So, I know what it feels like
to have someone living far away from you.

520
00:33:12,094 --> 00:33:14,763
Mm. So you're spying on me. Huh?

521
00:33:14,847 --> 00:33:16,974
-I know you've…
-I only just found out from Gibo.

522
00:33:17,057 --> 00:33:18,350
Talk to Gibo.

523
00:33:18,934 --> 00:33:20,936
-Spying. Who? Me?
-[laughs]

524
00:33:22,563 --> 00:33:27,234
Um, yeah. Okay, I've been…
emailing my dad.

525
00:33:27,985 --> 00:33:29,236
He's in the US.

526
00:33:31,447 --> 00:33:33,407
I'm trying to make him get me out of here.

527
00:33:35,325 --> 00:33:38,620
-Well, email him every day. Hm?
-Yeah.

528
00:33:39,496 --> 00:33:44,293
Then he can look after you.
That'll get rid of one burden for me.

529
00:33:44,376 --> 00:33:45,753
What'd you say? Huh?

530
00:33:46,587 --> 00:33:48,422
-Nothing. I said nothing.
-Yeah?

531
00:33:48,505 --> 00:33:50,340
-I thought so.
-Let's go.

532
00:33:50,424 --> 00:33:51,967
I thought so!

533
00:33:54,470 --> 00:33:55,846
[Rose] This is a lot.

534
00:33:57,765 --> 00:34:00,476
You know, I'll hand it to you.

535
00:34:01,727 --> 00:34:03,729
I really admire your persistence.

536
00:34:03,812 --> 00:34:06,315
[laughs lightly] Yeah, it's…

537
00:34:07,983 --> 00:34:12,196
It's been two years.
I've been emailing him for two years now.

538
00:34:12,696 --> 00:34:15,866
And you know how I found his email…
two years ago?

539
00:34:16,366 --> 00:34:18,452
I was just looking
through my mom's drawer.

540
00:34:19,495 --> 00:34:21,580
That was the way I found his contact.

541
00:34:21,663 --> 00:34:24,958
What? He still hasn't replied?

542
00:34:28,295 --> 00:34:31,256
Perhaps it's not even
his actual email address.

543
00:34:31,340 --> 00:34:34,218
-Maybe it belongs to someone else.
-No. I'm sure.

544
00:34:34,927 --> 00:34:36,470
I'm sure it's him, sorry.

545
00:34:37,346 --> 00:34:38,388
I lied.

546
00:34:41,350 --> 00:34:42,768
He did reply.

547
00:34:44,436 --> 00:34:46,605
But only to the first few emails.

548
00:34:46,688 --> 00:34:49,108
What if he's busy?

549
00:34:50,359 --> 00:34:53,278
Or he just forgot to reply?

550
00:34:54,488 --> 00:34:58,575
Or maybe he got annoyed.
You have been sending a lot of emails.

551
00:34:58,659 --> 00:35:00,327
Can you blame me?

552
00:35:04,957 --> 00:35:05,999
I…

553
00:35:07,543 --> 00:35:08,919
I just need my dad.

554
00:35:12,131 --> 00:35:14,383
So it's been how long now?

555
00:35:17,845 --> 00:35:18,887
Ten years.

556
00:35:22,057 --> 00:35:23,725
It's been ten years.

557
00:35:24,434 --> 00:35:25,936
I was seven years old.

558
00:35:35,404 --> 00:35:36,780
That's terrible.

559
00:35:37,990 --> 00:35:39,241
So long.

560
00:35:40,576 --> 00:35:45,789
But you still want your dad to take you?
Why? What's there in the US?

561
00:35:46,790 --> 00:35:50,252
Have you thought about that?
That you'll miss people.

562
00:35:50,335 --> 00:35:52,629
Your friends in the old Philippines.

563
00:35:55,257 --> 00:35:56,675
I don't have friends.

564
00:35:58,844 --> 00:36:01,889
Ah… Of course not.

565
00:36:03,640 --> 00:36:04,683
Of course not.

566
00:36:06,310 --> 00:36:08,520
-[keyboard clacking]
-[music fades]

567
00:36:10,480 --> 00:36:12,441
You know, I was thinking…

568
00:36:12,941 --> 00:36:17,821
Could your dad not want you
because you're… a bit desperate?

569
00:36:19,198 --> 00:36:23,869
-Well, I am desperate. Can't help that.
-Guess you can't.

570
00:36:23,952 --> 00:36:27,789
But have a think about Gela
and the girls' behavior. You hate it.

571
00:36:27,873 --> 00:36:29,958
They're desperate
for any attention from you.

572
00:36:30,042 --> 00:36:33,045
And the last thing
you want to do is give them that.

573
00:36:33,128 --> 00:36:36,089
-See? Get it now?
-Why are you comparing Gela to my dad?

574
00:36:36,173 --> 00:36:38,675
You want me to run away?
You want me to avoid him?

575
00:36:38,759 --> 00:36:42,137
-Ignore him? What are you…
-Well… No.

576
00:36:42,221 --> 00:36:45,724
Uh… You have to make him want you. Get it?

577
00:36:45,807 --> 00:36:49,186
Forget about how much
you have to talk to him.

578
00:36:49,269 --> 00:36:51,730
You shouldn't make him feel responsible.

579
00:36:52,231 --> 00:36:56,360
-Okay?
-But I am his responsibility. I'm his son.

580
00:36:56,860 --> 00:36:58,904
Where… where are you going with this?

581
00:36:59,613 --> 00:37:03,825
-You're so negative. I give up.
-Okay. Fine, fine. I'm listening.

582
00:37:03,909 --> 00:37:05,744
-That's enough. Forget it.
-I'm listening.

583
00:37:05,827 --> 00:37:09,957
Rose, I'm all ears.
Please. What do you suggest?

584
00:37:10,624 --> 00:37:12,125
[Rose clears throat]

585
00:37:12,209 --> 00:37:17,839
You have to make him see
that you have your life together, okay?

586
00:37:17,923 --> 00:37:21,927
That you're always busy,
that you're achieving many things.

587
00:37:22,010 --> 00:37:24,221
You have to be somebody. Huh?

588
00:37:24,304 --> 00:37:27,099
And how am I supposed to do that? Here, I…

589
00:37:27,599 --> 00:37:29,518
Very good question.

590
00:37:29,601 --> 00:37:33,605
Good question. You're really coming along.
All right. Eyes here, eyes here.

591
00:37:33,689 --> 00:37:36,733
Do you see that?
This picture here, do you know Mr. Chito?

592
00:37:36,817 --> 00:37:40,570
-Obviously not.
-This… this… this is Mr. Chito, here.

593
00:37:41,071 --> 00:37:43,282
This is Mr. Chito, who is now a councilor.

594
00:37:43,365 --> 00:37:47,786
Mr. Chito is also my uncle.
He's the owner of Green Skies.

595
00:37:47,869 --> 00:37:52,040
But… I'm the reason that he won.
He wouldn't have won, you see.

596
00:37:52,124 --> 00:37:55,168
Except I designed him
a poster and a jingle.

597
00:37:55,252 --> 00:38:00,132
Do you see? He became somebody.
Now I can do that too, for you.

598
00:38:01,508 --> 00:38:03,218
You just have to pay me.

599
00:38:04,845 --> 00:38:06,305
[Jordan laughs]

600
00:38:07,347 --> 00:38:10,183
You sound and look
like a scammer at the moment.

601
00:38:10,267 --> 00:38:12,561
Scammer, huh? Well, you get nothing.

602
00:38:14,187 --> 00:38:15,439
It's not a scam.

603
00:38:17,232 --> 00:38:19,234
And I don't charge high fees.

604
00:38:19,943 --> 00:38:22,863
-Deal?
-What do you need the money for anyway?

605
00:38:23,363 --> 00:38:24,573
You work here.

606
00:38:27,868 --> 00:38:29,995
I'm saving up for my debut.

607
00:38:30,996 --> 00:38:34,916
De-boo? De-boo. You mean debut?

608
00:38:37,085 --> 00:38:40,422
Debut. De-boo,
whatever, it's all the same.

609
00:38:40,505 --> 00:38:41,548
Sure.

610
00:38:42,215 --> 00:38:46,678
So you wanna…
wear a dress, dance with boys.

611
00:38:47,179 --> 00:38:49,848
-That's what you're saving money for?
-Hey.

612
00:38:50,766 --> 00:38:55,145
It's not that superficial.
In fact, it's every Filipina's dream.

613
00:38:56,355 --> 00:39:01,902
Maybe that's why Filipinas…
Filipinos don't have money. Hm?

614
00:39:02,402 --> 00:39:05,405
Sounds impractical.
Very impractical if you ask me.

615
00:39:05,489 --> 00:39:08,158
You and your mouth.
You should listen to yourself, man.

616
00:39:08,241 --> 00:39:12,371
You act like you're too cool for school,
but you're an American living here. Oh.

617
00:39:12,454 --> 00:39:14,289
Hey, how many times you gotta talk about…

618
00:39:14,373 --> 00:39:16,750
-That's because my dad left and I don't--
-[blows raspberry]

619
00:39:17,250 --> 00:39:21,421
Whatever. You talk too much.
So why don't you…

620
00:39:21,922 --> 00:39:28,428
just help me with the costs for my de-boo,
and you'll get my help reaching Daddy-o.

621
00:39:28,970 --> 00:39:31,973
Huh? Ah, ah!

622
00:39:38,897 --> 00:39:39,940
I don't know.

623
00:39:40,816 --> 00:39:44,611
Okay, money back
if it doesn't work. That's my offer.

624
00:39:48,615 --> 00:39:53,120
Mmm? Uh? Yeah! Good, right! Give it here.

625
00:39:53,620 --> 00:39:56,581
To quote that old saying,
"Are you in or out?"

626
00:39:57,416 --> 00:39:59,376
Huh? Give it here!

627
00:40:00,669 --> 00:40:06,299
-Fine. I'm in.
-Yeah! A good decision.

628
00:40:06,383 --> 00:40:08,885
Smart choice. Have these. [laughs]

629
00:40:10,762 --> 00:40:12,097
[music fades]

630
00:40:12,180 --> 00:40:14,558
-If your head hurts, stop doing it.
-Dad?

631
00:40:14,641 --> 00:40:16,101
Here, your daughter's home.

632
00:40:16,184 --> 00:40:18,895
-Here, it's your mother. She wants a word.
-Ah, thanks.

633
00:40:18,979 --> 00:40:20,188
Hey, Ma!

634
00:40:20,272 --> 00:40:24,484
Hey, I miss you. I love you, Ma.
I love you so, so, so much!

635
00:40:24,568 --> 00:40:28,697
Oh, honey, that's very nice to hear.
I love you too.

636
00:40:28,780 --> 00:40:30,323
You sound in good spirits.

637
00:40:30,824 --> 00:40:33,452
It's nothing, Ma.
I just found an extra racket.

638
00:40:33,535 --> 00:40:38,165
Hey, I'm not working hard over here
just so you can take on more side hustles.

639
00:40:38,248 --> 00:40:39,708
My debut's soon.

640
00:40:40,667 --> 00:40:43,545
-Will you be here for that?
-Of course I will.

641
00:40:43,628 --> 00:40:47,424
Oh, and do you have a list of men
that are going to dance with you?

642
00:40:48,216 --> 00:40:49,426
Come on, a list?

643
00:40:49,509 --> 00:40:52,387
And find someone handsome.
That shouldn't be hard.

644
00:40:52,471 --> 00:40:56,057
Listen to her!
She thinks I should look for a male model.

645
00:40:57,809 --> 00:41:00,937
This is our strategy if we're
going to get your dad to notice you.

646
00:41:01,021 --> 00:41:02,981
1. GET RECOGNITION AT SCHOOL

647
00:41:03,064 --> 00:41:07,027
-Here it is.
-Serious? I'm paying for this?

648
00:41:08,445 --> 00:41:10,655
You know, I've been working on this a lot.

649
00:41:10,739 --> 00:41:13,158
So, you better choose
your next words carefully.

650
00:41:13,658 --> 00:41:16,620
Number three. All right, "Become famous."

651
00:41:16,703 --> 00:41:19,831
-"And be seen on live TV. "
-Mm.

652
00:41:20,624 --> 00:41:21,875
How are we supposed to do that?

653
00:41:21,958 --> 00:41:25,086
You're such a downer all the time.
Why be a downer?

654
00:41:25,170 --> 00:41:28,715
-Don't worry about that. I'll work it out.
-Fine.

655
00:41:29,299 --> 00:41:34,054
I'll leave all the work to you,
Ms. Miracle Worker.

656
00:41:34,137 --> 00:41:37,265
Yes! That's the spirit!

657
00:41:38,058 --> 00:41:40,060
-I'm ready to get my money back.
-Say what?

658
00:41:40,143 --> 00:41:43,104
Nothing! Nothing.

659
00:41:43,188 --> 00:41:46,024
Come on. Where do we start?

660
00:41:48,151 --> 00:41:51,363
Now, relax. Anyway, this plan's great.

661
00:41:52,030 --> 00:41:57,077
You're gonna be
the next student body president.

662
00:41:57,160 --> 00:42:00,830
Rose, I'm a transferee.
No one's going to vote for me.

663
00:42:01,331 --> 00:42:05,168
Oh, really? That you can't ever know.

664
00:42:06,586 --> 00:42:08,421
[upbeat pop music playing]

665
00:42:10,423 --> 00:42:13,843
You smile. Big smile. Yeah!

666
00:42:13,927 --> 00:42:16,596
Then you wave to them.
Just wave to them, go.

667
00:42:16,680 --> 00:42:19,432
-Girls!
-[screams]

668
00:42:20,100 --> 00:42:21,893
[screaming grows louder]

669
00:42:21,977 --> 00:42:25,188
Ah! Now, you tell them, "Wow, I love you!"

670
00:42:25,272 --> 00:42:27,941
-All right, now, why would I say that?
-[screaming continues]

671
00:42:28,024 --> 00:42:31,194
Don't be a downer.
Say, "Wow, I love you!" Shout.

672
00:42:32,320 --> 00:42:34,906
-[half-heartedly] Wow! I love you!
-[screaming intensifies]

673
00:42:36,324 --> 00:42:39,661
-Oh!
-[all] We love you, Jordan!

674
00:42:39,744 --> 00:42:42,414
-[gang yelling excitedly]
-[Rose laughs]

675
00:42:42,497 --> 00:42:47,127
-[upbeat pop music continues]
-Oh! All right.

676
00:42:47,210 --> 00:42:48,211
[Rose] Let's get to work.

677
00:42:48,712 --> 00:42:51,464
Go easy on the orders, Rose.
We're not getting paid.

678
00:42:51,548 --> 00:42:52,757
Damn right.

679
00:42:52,841 --> 00:42:55,927
Oh. It sounds like
you want me to go and get Jordan.

680
00:42:56,011 --> 00:42:57,345
Could that be what you're saying?

681
00:42:57,429 --> 00:42:59,723
-No, no, I didn't say that.
-Jordan!

682
00:42:59,806 --> 00:43:01,766
-Yeah. Just a sec. What's up?
-[Rose] Mm.

683
00:43:01,850 --> 00:43:05,353
Jordan, what's that?
Is that dirt in your armpits?

684
00:43:05,437 --> 00:43:06,521
Check them.

685
00:43:07,022 --> 00:43:09,983
-[screams]
-[boy] Oh my God.

686
00:43:10,066 --> 00:43:11,985
-[screaming continues]
-Oh my God!

687
00:43:12,068 --> 00:43:13,778
[Gela] Now, we'll work, work, work.

688
00:43:15,655 --> 00:43:17,240
-Vote for Jordan.
-Vote for me.

689
00:43:17,324 --> 00:43:19,159
You have to vote for him.
Tell your friends.

690
00:43:19,242 --> 00:43:21,745
-Casey! Oh, can you hold this?
-[girl] Vote for Jordan!

691
00:43:21,828 --> 00:43:23,955
When the gang arrives,
can you give it to them?

692
00:43:24,539 --> 00:43:27,208
And then, I'll let you know
what I want you to do.

693
00:43:27,709 --> 00:43:29,169
-Just hold on. Thanks for this.
-Rose.

694
00:43:29,252 --> 00:43:31,504
Yeah. Thank you. Take care.

695
00:43:31,588 --> 00:43:32,881
What is it?

696
00:43:33,632 --> 00:43:36,760
-I'm giving away flyers and balloons.
-Yeah, can't you do that next to me?

697
00:43:38,887 --> 00:43:39,846
Why?

698
00:43:39,929 --> 00:43:41,348
'Cause I need you.

699
00:43:42,807 --> 00:43:46,811
Uh, I need my campaign manager. Hm?!

700
00:43:49,397 --> 00:43:50,440
Sure.

701
00:43:51,107 --> 00:43:56,029
-Jordan! Jordan! Jordan for president!
-[upbeat pop music continues]

702
00:43:56,112 --> 00:43:57,155
[Jordan laughs]

703
00:43:57,238 --> 00:43:59,991
-Submit it!
-[Jordan] I'm going to do it!

704
00:44:00,075 --> 00:44:02,744
Um… Ma'am. Jordan Anderson.

705
00:44:02,827 --> 00:44:04,996
Please. Can I please take the photo?

706
00:44:05,997 --> 00:44:08,333
-One, two, three…
-[inaudible]

707
00:44:12,212 --> 00:44:15,006
[upbeat pop music continues]

708
00:44:24,391 --> 00:44:25,975
[pop music fades]

709
00:44:28,395 --> 00:44:30,271
[rooster crows in distance]

710
00:44:36,820 --> 00:44:42,409
-[inspiring music playing]
-Oh! Beautiful! [gasps]

711
00:44:43,493 --> 00:44:44,536
Oh.

712
00:44:48,373 --> 00:44:50,583
-That one's beautiful.
-[Rose] It is!

713
00:44:50,667 --> 00:44:51,876
And I think it suits you.

714
00:44:51,960 --> 00:44:55,922
But maybe you'd consider
offering a discount for friends?

715
00:44:56,005 --> 00:44:58,383
Um, I'll see. I could ask my mother.

716
00:44:58,466 --> 00:44:59,968
-Promise?
-Yes, of course.

717
00:45:00,051 --> 00:45:02,887
By the way,
it's weird you're not here with Jordan.

718
00:45:02,971 --> 00:45:07,100
Why? Because if he was,
you'd give that discount for sure?

719
00:45:07,183 --> 00:45:09,519
-Who, me?
-[both chuckle]

720
00:45:09,602 --> 00:45:10,979
But he'll need to be measured up

721
00:45:11,062 --> 00:45:13,273
for what he's wearing
to the meeting about the election.

722
00:45:13,356 --> 00:45:15,650
No, it's not hard to do.

723
00:45:15,734 --> 00:45:18,111
-I can guess it and, anyway, he's busy.
-Ah.

724
00:45:18,194 --> 00:45:20,947
Because right now,
he's practicing his speech.

725
00:45:21,030 --> 00:45:23,575
-A speech, I see.
-A speech!

726
00:45:23,658 --> 00:45:26,786
But… are you officially
going out with Jordan?

727
00:45:27,370 --> 00:45:29,330
You two are always together, right?

728
00:45:29,914 --> 00:45:32,959
-Yuck! No, that's silly.
-Yeah. [laughs]

729
00:45:33,042 --> 00:45:35,879
-That's not a thing. That'd never happen.
-Really?

730
00:45:35,962 --> 00:45:40,216
But anyway,
I just want to assist with the election.

731
00:45:40,842 --> 00:45:44,554
-[Gela] Mmm.
-I don't know if… we're even friends.

732
00:45:44,637 --> 00:45:46,723
You're only saying that.

733
00:45:46,806 --> 00:45:50,894
Maybe you're just giving
false hope to us Jordan addicts.

734
00:45:50,977 --> 00:45:53,646
[laughs] Jordan addicts.

735
00:45:53,730 --> 00:45:54,814
Oh, and of course,

736
00:45:54,898 --> 00:45:57,776
if it's the wrong size
or doesn't fit, just bring it back.

737
00:46:01,863 --> 00:46:03,990
[music fades]

738
00:46:05,742 --> 00:46:06,785
Anderson!

739
00:46:08,077 --> 00:46:09,913
-Dimaguiba!
-[cheers]

740
00:46:10,830 --> 00:46:12,749
-Anderson!
-[Jordan] It's close.

741
00:46:13,500 --> 00:46:14,834
Dimaguiba!

742
00:46:14,918 --> 00:46:17,086
-Why are you so nervous?
-[Ms. Melai] Anderson!

743
00:46:17,712 --> 00:46:18,880
-Dimaguiba!
-I'm not.

744
00:46:18,963 --> 00:46:21,925
-Rose, you're literally biting your nails.
-[Ms. Melai] Anderson!

745
00:46:22,675 --> 00:46:23,718
What's up?

746
00:46:23,802 --> 00:46:26,054
-[Ms. Melai] Dimaguiba!
-I'm okay. I'm just hungry.

747
00:46:27,055 --> 00:46:28,181
[Ms. Melai] Anderson!

748
00:46:28,264 --> 00:46:30,558
-Joke!
-[Ms. Melai] Dimaguiba!

749
00:46:31,309 --> 00:46:34,270
[exhales] It's because
it's such a close fight, see?

750
00:46:34,771 --> 00:46:37,023
I thought it was gonna be a landslide.

751
00:46:37,106 --> 00:46:38,775
-[Ms. Melai] Anderson!
-I hope you win.

752
00:46:38,858 --> 00:46:40,193
[Ms. Melai] Dimaguiba!

753
00:46:40,693 --> 00:46:43,446
-[Ms. Melai] Anderson! Dimaguiba!
-Don't worry. I'll win.

754
00:46:43,530 --> 00:46:45,323
-I'm sure about it.
-[Ms. Melai] Anderson!

755
00:46:45,406 --> 00:46:47,909
What self-belief. Confident!

756
00:46:47,992 --> 00:46:50,203
-[Ms. Melai] Anderson!
-Maybe we'll get knocked out?

757
00:46:50,286 --> 00:46:52,664
-No. That's impossible.
-[Ms. Melai] Dimaguiba!

758
00:46:52,747 --> 00:46:57,126
You know why? Because I have
the best campaign manager in the world.

759
00:46:57,210 --> 00:46:59,087
-[poignant music playing]
-[Ms. Melai] Anderson!

760
00:46:59,170 --> 00:47:00,463
[cheering]

761
00:47:00,547 --> 00:47:02,799
-[Ms. Melai] Dimaguiba!
-[applause]

762
00:47:02,882 --> 00:47:05,176
[Ms. Melai] There's five more,
just five more.

763
00:47:05,677 --> 00:47:07,262
-Shh.
-Dimaguiba!

764
00:47:08,096 --> 00:47:09,055
[cheers]

765
00:47:09,138 --> 00:47:10,974
-[nervous chatter]
-Anderson!

766
00:47:11,057 --> 00:47:13,560
-[all] Yes!
-Dimaguiba!

767
00:47:15,770 --> 00:47:16,646
Anderson!

768
00:47:17,480 --> 00:47:19,107
-[cheering]
-Yes!

769
00:47:19,190 --> 00:47:21,192
[tense music playing]

770
00:47:22,026 --> 00:47:23,403
-Anderson!
-[cheering]

771
00:47:23,486 --> 00:47:25,864
[Ms. Melai] Okay!
We have a new student council president.

772
00:47:25,947 --> 00:47:28,408
It's the transferee, Jordan Anderson!

773
00:47:29,576 --> 00:47:31,870
[raucous cheering]

774
00:47:31,953 --> 00:47:34,539
[upbeat pop music playing]

775
00:47:40,670 --> 00:47:42,505
[all] Jordan!

776
00:47:42,589 --> 00:47:46,301
[cheering continues]

777
00:47:47,635 --> 00:47:51,097
[all] Jordan! Jordan! Jordan! Jordan!

778
00:47:51,180 --> 00:47:53,099
Jordan! Jordan!

779
00:47:53,182 --> 00:47:55,018
1. GET RECOGNITION AT SCHOOL

780
00:47:55,101 --> 00:47:57,020
[all] Jordan! Jordan!

781
00:47:57,103 --> 00:47:59,522
-Hey! Take it easy.
-[laughs]

782
00:47:59,606 --> 00:48:01,232
People might think
you're losing your mind.

783
00:48:01,316 --> 00:48:05,945
No, I… I just didn't know I could be
this happy from winning the election.

784
00:48:06,446 --> 00:48:08,406
-Can we go to Green Skies?
-Now?

785
00:48:08,489 --> 00:48:11,910
Yeah. I was thinking I want
to message my dad as soon as I can.

786
00:48:12,410 --> 00:48:16,331
Well, the shop's closed today.
They're fixing the modem.

787
00:48:16,831 --> 00:48:18,625
-Are you serious?
-Mm-hmm.

788
00:48:18,708 --> 00:48:21,127
There's no way. Damn.

789
00:48:21,711 --> 00:48:25,757
It's okay. Don't worry,
it'll be open again early tomorrow.

790
00:48:25,840 --> 00:48:27,550
You'll be able to email your dad then.

791
00:48:27,634 --> 00:48:29,052
-Wait. You'd do that for me?
-Mmm.

792
00:48:29,135 --> 00:48:31,095
-You would do that for me?
-Yeah.

793
00:48:31,179 --> 00:48:34,474
-You'll be able to email. It'll be fine.
-Best campaign manager ever!

794
00:48:34,557 --> 00:48:37,310
-[Jordan laughing]
-Hey, quit it. If I punched you…

795
00:48:37,393 --> 00:48:39,145
-Agh, oh…
-[clack]

796
00:48:39,228 --> 00:48:42,023
-Oh, careful, you'll break it.
-Oh, damn!

797
00:48:42,106 --> 00:48:44,901
-That's sore. Ugh, it's your fault.
-[music turns somber]

798
00:48:44,984 --> 00:48:46,444
You don't look okay.

799
00:48:46,527 --> 00:48:48,279
It's your fault I'm so dizzy.

800
00:48:48,363 --> 00:48:52,450
[laughs] Sorry, oh… Well, you can't walk.

801
00:48:52,533 --> 00:48:55,286
-Made me dizzy, spinning me round.
-I can carry you. Come on. One…

802
00:48:55,370 --> 00:48:58,873
-Two…
-Don't overreact. I need to sit down.

803
00:48:59,457 --> 00:49:00,750
-Okay.
-Okay?

804
00:49:01,501 --> 00:49:05,463
-Ah, you're catching on fast!
-[both laugh]

805
00:49:06,673 --> 00:49:09,092
You know, when Dad and I lived in Manila,

806
00:49:09,175 --> 00:49:11,678
I thought I should
have started working earlier,

807
00:49:11,761 --> 00:49:15,098
because I wanted to do
what they were doing on TV.

808
00:49:15,181 --> 00:49:17,642
You know Star Circle Quest? Kids.

809
00:49:17,725 --> 00:49:19,519
Kid's Quest. I could have done it.

810
00:49:19,602 --> 00:49:22,146
If I'd done that,
then by now we'd be rich.

811
00:49:22,230 --> 00:49:23,439
You think those kids are rich?

812
00:49:23,523 --> 00:49:27,610
Don't you? Of course.
You're gonna be modeling Moose Gear.

813
00:49:27,694 --> 00:49:30,863
Then you'll get deals for hot dogs. Oh!

814
00:49:30,947 --> 00:49:33,992
Now, that'd be all right,
a lifetime supply of hot dogs!

815
00:49:34,075 --> 00:49:36,953
[laughs] Maybe I should be an actor.

816
00:49:37,036 --> 00:49:40,540
-You? That'd suit you!
-[laughs]

817
00:49:40,623 --> 00:49:43,543
-Oh, yeah! You look like one!
-Yeah?

818
00:49:43,626 --> 00:49:45,920
Seriously though,
Filipinas are into that stuff.

819
00:49:46,004 --> 00:49:48,965
You know,
foreigners and looking like foreigners.

820
00:49:49,048 --> 00:49:52,010
Sandara Park is a foreigner
and she won SCQ.

821
00:49:52,093 --> 00:49:55,304
-Mm.
-You didn't know that before? Mm?

822
00:49:55,388 --> 00:49:56,848
-Mm?
-No. [laughs]

823
00:49:58,016 --> 00:50:00,852
Yeah, but why would
you want to be an actor?

824
00:50:00,935 --> 00:50:04,647
Would you still work?
Your father lives in the US.

825
00:50:04,731 --> 00:50:06,482
He'd probably send you lots of money.

826
00:50:10,153 --> 00:50:13,239
-[poignant music playing]
-Huh.

827
00:50:15,408 --> 00:50:16,451
-Hm.
-What?

828
00:50:17,910 --> 00:50:18,911
Doesn't he?

829
00:50:20,830 --> 00:50:22,415
Come to think of it, I…

830
00:50:23,833 --> 00:50:25,293
I honestly wouldn't know.

831
00:50:27,128 --> 00:50:30,131
Mom never talked about Dad sending money.

832
00:50:32,091 --> 00:50:35,053
You've got a problem
if you want to follow this dude.

833
00:50:35,136 --> 00:50:36,888
Why do you want to be over there?

834
00:50:40,850 --> 00:50:44,228
Mmm… I don't know, I guess…

835
00:50:46,105 --> 00:50:48,691
Ever since I was a kid,
my dad was my hero.

836
00:50:50,485 --> 00:50:54,614
Just wanted to be like him. I idolized him
in every single way I could think of.

837
00:50:54,697 --> 00:50:56,574
Whatever he did, I wanted to do.

838
00:50:57,075 --> 00:51:00,036
Is that why you became a blonde, huh?

839
00:51:00,119 --> 00:51:01,954
-And why the fake accent?
-What?

840
00:51:02,038 --> 00:51:04,707
That blonde.
The blonde is fake. Yeah! [laughs]

841
00:51:04,791 --> 00:51:06,751
-This is not… This is real.
-Oh!

842
00:51:06,834 --> 00:51:09,879
-It's not. You can see here, it's fake.
-This is… [laughs]

843
00:51:09,962 --> 00:51:11,923
Okay! Fine. Fine.

844
00:51:12,715 --> 00:51:15,384
Fine. Yes, Okay. Fine, fine, fine.

845
00:51:15,968 --> 00:51:22,475
Fake hair, fake Tagalog accent.
I can talk Tagalog pretty good, but…

846
00:51:24,435 --> 00:51:28,439
I don't know. I guess I got used
to speaking English all my life 'cause…

847
00:51:29,065 --> 00:51:30,733
Yeah, Dad spoke English.

848
00:51:31,234 --> 00:51:35,404
Like I said, anything he did,
everything he did, I followed, I copied.

849
00:51:36,239 --> 00:51:38,157
I faked it until…

850
00:51:39,492 --> 00:51:40,785
it made me happy.

851
00:51:41,702 --> 00:51:43,037
Well…

852
00:51:46,124 --> 00:51:47,208
Yeah.

853
00:51:48,209 --> 00:51:50,545
And are you happy now?

854
00:51:53,005 --> 00:51:54,006
Hm?

855
00:51:54,799 --> 00:51:57,218
[poignant music continues]

856
00:52:00,388 --> 00:52:01,764
Now I am.

857
00:52:02,306 --> 00:52:03,933
-Ah!
-A little.

858
00:52:04,016 --> 00:52:07,895
-Hey, thanks to me. Thanks to me!
-Thanks to you.

859
00:52:08,646 --> 00:52:09,564
And…

860
00:52:11,190 --> 00:52:12,150
You're welcome.

861
00:52:59,238 --> 00:53:00,406
[music stops]

862
00:53:05,203 --> 00:53:08,414
Man, it's been two days. Still no reply.

863
00:53:09,373 --> 00:53:13,169
Hey, face facts.
Maybe he's been busy with work.

864
00:53:13,252 --> 00:53:17,048
It could be too busy to check emails.
You don't know.

865
00:53:20,801 --> 00:53:24,889
-I knew this wouldn't work.
-Hey, come on. Calm down.

866
00:53:25,389 --> 00:53:28,351
This is just the first plan.
We've got two more on the list, right?

867
00:53:28,434 --> 00:53:30,853
Think positive, okay? All right?

868
00:53:30,937 --> 00:53:33,564
-Sorry, you're right. Think positive.
-Mm.

869
00:53:33,648 --> 00:53:35,107
-That's right.
-Attract positivity.

870
00:53:35,191 --> 00:53:37,818
That's right. Now, because
you've been very good, have a treat.

871
00:53:39,570 --> 00:53:40,655
That's it!

872
00:53:41,239 --> 00:53:45,034
Ah! How come you and Putrid
are together so often?

873
00:53:45,117 --> 00:53:47,620
I thought you were
just helping with the election.

874
00:53:48,120 --> 00:53:49,372
Who's Putrid?

875
00:53:49,455 --> 00:53:50,581
-You!
-You!

876
00:53:50,665 --> 00:53:54,377
-Hey. He doesn't smell, you know.
-[Gibo laughing] Uh…

877
00:53:54,877 --> 00:53:57,129
-[boy 1] She said he doesn't smell!
-Stop it, okay?

878
00:53:57,213 --> 00:54:00,424
-[boys laughing]
-Hey, that's enough, guys.

879
00:54:00,508 --> 00:54:03,511
-Come in, come in.
-[Gibo] So he doesn't smell anymore? Ugh.

880
00:54:03,594 --> 00:54:06,681
You can help us out
instead of acting all stupid.

881
00:54:06,764 --> 00:54:08,015
We've got a problem here.

882
00:54:08,099 --> 00:54:11,686
We have to make this guy famous.
So maybe suggest something. An idea or…

883
00:54:11,769 --> 00:54:14,897
Oh, I saw this on TV.
A guy opening a coconut with his teeth.

884
00:54:14,981 --> 00:54:16,148
-I saw that!
-That'd be great.

885
00:54:16,232 --> 00:54:17,817
What are you talking about, dude?

886
00:54:17,900 --> 00:54:20,486
-You. Coconut.
-Ah, you take the coconut…

887
00:54:20,569 --> 00:54:24,115
-Coconut mouth? Your ideas are stupid.
-[Gibo] Oh, come on, it'd be awesome.

888
00:54:24,198 --> 00:54:27,493
-Enough now. Don't listen to them.
-[Gibo] Why don't you try that?

889
00:54:27,576 --> 00:54:30,997
-Damn right! These suggestions are stupid.
-Tell me how that works out.

890
00:54:31,080 --> 00:54:33,040
Uh, excuse me, is Bertha here?

891
00:54:33,124 --> 00:54:34,709
-Uh, is this your dad?
-Bertha?

892
00:54:35,334 --> 00:54:36,961
-No.
-We're under attack from white people!

893
00:54:37,044 --> 00:54:40,006
Don't… don't mind them.
Jordan. How can I help you?

894
00:54:40,089 --> 00:54:42,800
Yeah, I'm looking
for a woman named Bertha.

895
00:54:43,301 --> 00:54:46,679
-[Jordan] I'm new here, so I don't know.
-[Rose] Uh, maybe…

896
00:54:46,762 --> 00:54:48,931
-Who's Bertha?
-Do you have her address?

897
00:54:49,432 --> 00:54:52,476
Well, this is the only
Internet café in town, right?

898
00:54:52,560 --> 00:54:54,228
-Yeah, yeah.
-[Rose] Only this one.

899
00:54:54,312 --> 00:54:58,107
Then I'm sure she's from here.
Sorry, sir, I didn't get your name.

900
00:54:58,190 --> 00:55:00,067
Uh, I'm sorry, my name is Ewan.

901
00:55:00,151 --> 00:55:01,861
-That's familiar to you?
-[Ewan] See this.

902
00:55:01,944 --> 00:55:06,324
I always see this in the background
when we chat on Yahoo Messenger, so…

903
00:55:06,824 --> 00:55:11,078
-She's got to be from here.
-Ah! You're the one she always speaks to!

904
00:55:11,162 --> 00:55:12,705
You're Ms. Berta's baby.

905
00:55:12,788 --> 00:55:14,248
-Berta! Yes, Berta!
-It's you.

906
00:55:14,332 --> 00:55:16,500
-Ah, Berta!
-[Rose] I remember your face.

907
00:55:16,584 --> 00:55:19,837
I'm here to surprise her.
Do you know where she lives?

908
00:55:19,920 --> 00:55:22,048
I will take you to her.

909
00:55:22,131 --> 00:55:23,883
-Great! Great, great!
-I got you.

910
00:55:23,966 --> 00:55:25,926
-Okay, come on.
-Can you three look after the shop

911
00:55:26,010 --> 00:55:28,012
-while I take this guy to Ms. Berta?
-[boys] Sure.

912
00:55:28,095 --> 00:55:29,388
-Let's go.
-Hurry!

913
00:55:30,056 --> 00:55:32,099
-[Ewan] There. There. Yeah.
-[Rose] It's here.

914
00:55:34,602 --> 00:55:36,729
[exciting music playing]

915
00:55:37,813 --> 00:55:39,398
RomblonPrettyGirl!

916
00:55:39,482 --> 00:55:41,942
[music turns intriguing]

917
00:55:42,026 --> 00:55:44,653
DaddyWhiteBoy19?!

918
00:55:44,737 --> 00:55:46,697
-Bertha!
-Ewan!

919
00:55:46,781 --> 00:55:49,658
Yes, it's me!
I came here to be with you, my love!

920
00:55:49,742 --> 00:55:54,163
-Oh my God! Oh my… Oh my God.
-[music stops]

921
00:55:54,246 --> 00:55:58,626
-Oh my God. Oh my God, oh my God…
-Wait there. Ms. Berta?

922
00:55:58,709 --> 00:56:00,252
-What's going on?
-What the heck?

923
00:56:00,336 --> 00:56:03,672
Oh my God, oh my God, oh my God! [whines]

924
00:56:03,756 --> 00:56:07,676
[whimpers] Oh my God! Am I beautiful?

925
00:56:07,760 --> 00:56:10,721
-Of course you are. So pretty.
-Really?

926
00:56:10,805 --> 00:56:15,518
Look at me. Look at me, I'm hideous.
You're hideous, aren't you? You're awful.

927
00:56:15,601 --> 00:56:17,853
-Come on, Ms. Berta.
-[cries]

928
00:56:17,937 --> 00:56:21,399
[Rose] Have you forgotten?
You're the original jewel of Romblon.

929
00:56:22,483 --> 00:56:23,984
Those days are gone.

930
00:56:24,485 --> 00:56:28,864
But this is who I am now.
Oh, I've gotten so big, Rose.

931
00:56:28,948 --> 00:56:32,701
Why? Why?
Why would she run away like that?

932
00:56:32,785 --> 00:56:35,287
Am I… am I that ugly? Do I smell bad?

933
00:56:35,371 --> 00:56:38,999
Hey, hey. Hey, hey.
Don't beat yourself up. Not just yet.

934
00:56:39,083 --> 00:56:43,337
-[Ewan sighs]
-It's just, you know, women are…

935
00:56:44,296 --> 00:56:46,757
weird, here. [laughs]

936
00:56:46,841 --> 00:56:51,220
That's what I like about her.
She's… different.

937
00:56:51,303 --> 00:56:53,389
I thought she would appreciate, uh…

938
00:56:53,889 --> 00:56:56,308
-a crazy surprise like this.
-Uh-huh.

939
00:56:56,392 --> 00:56:58,185
You know, because she's…

940
00:56:58,269 --> 00:56:59,353
-Crazy!
-Yeah.

941
00:56:59,437 --> 00:57:01,605
I just didn't think
she was going to be that crazy.

942
00:57:01,689 --> 00:57:04,567
Hey, don't worry about it too much, okay?
Rose is in there.

943
00:57:04,650 --> 00:57:06,902
She'll speak some… sense into her head.

944
00:57:07,611 --> 00:57:08,946
Rose is the best.

945
00:57:09,029 --> 00:57:12,199
Really? Rose is that good?

946
00:57:14,368 --> 00:57:15,619
-Yeah.
-[dramatic note plays]

947
00:57:15,703 --> 00:57:19,290
Shit, I'm so stressed.
I don't know what I should wear.

948
00:57:19,373 --> 00:57:21,375
[sighs] Do you like this one?

949
00:57:21,459 --> 00:57:23,627
-I think…
-No, it's ugly.

950
00:57:23,711 --> 00:57:25,212
I look like an ex-convent girl.

951
00:57:25,296 --> 00:57:27,798
-That will look so nice.
-Disgusting!

952
00:57:28,716 --> 00:57:30,301
Not this one!

953
00:57:30,384 --> 00:57:33,762
Don't worry. That man didn't
come here because of what you wear.

954
00:57:34,638 --> 00:57:36,974
-He's here to see you.
-[dramatic note plays]

955
00:57:37,057 --> 00:57:39,643
[melancholic music playing]

956
00:57:45,274 --> 00:57:47,985
He's just so good-looking.

957
00:57:49,862 --> 00:57:53,324
Well, Ewan… what's your plan now?

958
00:57:53,407 --> 00:57:55,117
I don't know! [laughs nervously]

959
00:57:56,285 --> 00:57:58,204
But I'm not giving up on her.

960
00:57:58,287 --> 00:58:00,581
You don't give up on love.

961
00:58:01,665 --> 00:58:02,708
Yeah.

962
00:58:04,543 --> 00:58:05,920
Have you ever been in love?

963
00:58:06,003 --> 00:58:08,005
[poignant music playing]

964
00:58:17,723 --> 00:58:19,058
Good morning, Ms.

965
00:58:19,892 --> 00:58:21,310
Where on earth have you been?

966
00:58:21,393 --> 00:58:25,397
-Hey, hey, hey… how's Bertha?
-[Rose sighs] Uh…

967
00:58:25,481 --> 00:58:27,650
She's just a bit overwhelmed.

968
00:58:27,733 --> 00:58:29,860
-Uh.
-Because, you see…

969
00:58:29,944 --> 00:58:34,907
She wasn't expecting at all that
you'd come all the way here, that's all.

970
00:58:34,990 --> 00:58:39,954
-Yeah, because I want to be with her.
-Maybe she's just… confused.

971
00:58:40,663 --> 00:58:44,083
I mean, we know
she loves the online version of you.

972
00:58:44,166 --> 00:58:47,336
-Okay, well, what… what can I do?
-Simple!

973
00:58:48,212 --> 00:58:51,715
We'll show her
and introduce to her the real you.

974
00:58:51,799 --> 00:58:54,176
-Okay… how do we do that?
-Okay?

975
00:58:54,260 --> 00:58:57,680
We'll do that
by getting you to sing harana to her.

976
00:58:57,763 --> 00:59:00,516
-Harana? What, what, what is that?
-Yes, we'll do harana.

977
00:59:00,599 --> 00:59:04,061
That's the traditional way
of courting here in the Philippines.

978
00:59:04,144 --> 00:59:05,813
-Okay, Okay.
-Okay? We'll do it?

979
00:59:05,896 --> 00:59:07,022
-Yes!
-Yes!

980
00:59:07,106 --> 00:59:07,940
Am I a part of this?

981
00:59:08,023 --> 00:59:10,276
-Yes, of course!
-Yeah, come on, I can't do this alone!

982
00:59:10,359 --> 00:59:12,027
-[Rose] Yes!
-[Ewan] There you go!

983
00:59:12,111 --> 00:59:15,114
You know… I can't believe

984
00:59:15,864 --> 00:59:20,703
that Ewan is willing
to give up his whole life in the States.

985
00:59:20,786 --> 00:59:21,912
-Whole life.
-[Rose] Mmm.

986
00:59:21,996 --> 00:59:24,957
And turn everything around for Ms. Berta.

987
00:59:25,749 --> 00:59:28,252
-Crazy.
-Really?

988
00:59:29,003 --> 00:59:33,757
I don't think so. I get Ewan.
Because he really loves Ms. Berta.

989
00:59:34,258 --> 00:59:37,428
And he's the sort of person
that, when he's in love,

990
00:59:37,511 --> 00:59:39,763
he won't stop till he's tried everything.

991
00:59:41,640 --> 00:59:43,517
Do you think that'd be your approach?

992
00:59:45,978 --> 00:59:47,021
I don't know.

993
00:59:49,231 --> 00:59:52,526
You don't know? Why?
Haven't you been in love?

994
00:59:55,237 --> 00:59:56,739
[pensive music playing]

995
00:59:59,450 --> 01:00:03,871
Ah, maybe you can't relate
because you've never felt love.

996
01:00:03,954 --> 01:00:05,873
That's why. What a loser.

997
01:00:05,956 --> 01:00:09,793
[scoffs] What? You're trying
to tell me you've been in love?

998
01:00:09,877 --> 01:00:11,420
Of course! Twice!

999
01:00:11,503 --> 01:00:12,671
-Twice?!
-Yeah!

1000
01:00:12,755 --> 01:00:13,631
Damn.

1001
01:00:13,714 --> 01:00:16,300
-Oh, yeah.
-Twice already, this early on in life?

1002
01:00:16,383 --> 01:00:18,385
You're trying to tell me
you've been in love twice.

1003
01:00:18,469 --> 01:00:22,514
Oh, what? You've never been in love.
You don't know. You've got no idea.

1004
01:00:23,015 --> 01:00:25,768
Someone falls in love easily. Mmm.

1005
01:00:25,851 --> 01:00:27,102
Ah… bu--bu--but…

1006
01:00:28,145 --> 01:00:30,189
[laughs] Careful.

1007
01:00:32,358 --> 01:00:34,109
You might fall in love with me!

1008
01:00:34,193 --> 01:00:37,613
-Hm?
-Uh… Oh, smooth!

1009
01:00:37,696 --> 01:00:41,033
-[laughs]
-You talk too much, you know! Okay.

1010
01:00:41,533 --> 01:00:45,412
There was one who was
a neighbor back in the day.

1011
01:00:45,496 --> 01:00:47,456
I was still in grade two.

1012
01:00:47,956 --> 01:00:51,794
But he moved to Manila.
And the other one's name was Jack.

1013
01:00:53,796 --> 01:00:55,964
-Jack?
-Of course, Jack.

1014
01:00:56,965 --> 01:00:58,926
Am I supposed to know who Jack is?

1015
01:00:59,426 --> 01:01:03,972
It's Jack. He's in the Titanic. [chuckles]

1016
01:01:04,056 --> 01:01:05,516
[Jordan laughs] Ah!

1017
01:01:06,725 --> 01:01:09,812
Spoiler alert… He died.

1018
01:01:10,396 --> 01:01:14,024
You're hopeless. Okay.
Why did he die then? Why did he die?

1019
01:01:15,734 --> 01:01:17,403
I don't know, the Titanic sank?

1020
01:01:17,486 --> 01:01:22,783
Hey. He sacrificed himself for Rose.
You get it?

1021
01:01:22,866 --> 01:01:27,746
And we've got the same name.
Damn! How's that?

1022
01:01:27,830 --> 01:01:29,832
[both laugh]

1023
01:01:29,915 --> 01:01:33,127
And, you know,
when Gela and the girls first saw you,

1024
01:01:33,210 --> 01:01:36,255
they said you looked
just like Leonardo DiCaprio.

1025
01:01:38,132 --> 01:01:40,843
Really? [groans, laughs]

1026
01:01:42,219 --> 01:01:45,597
-Ah! Da-da-da-da-da…
-What?

1027
01:01:45,681 --> 01:01:46,932
I understand it now.

1028
01:01:47,015 --> 01:01:50,728
You say I look like Leonardo DiCaprio.

1029
01:01:50,811 --> 01:01:52,688
Jack. Mm.

1030
01:01:53,480 --> 01:01:56,608
You're trying to tell me
you have a crush on me?

1031
01:01:57,526 --> 01:02:01,238
Uh, excuse me.
It was actually Gela who said that.

1032
01:02:01,321 --> 01:02:03,741
-Mmm.
-Oh, I don't see it.

1033
01:02:03,824 --> 01:02:07,327
-I don't see it. There or there!
-Oh… Oh, ah… Ah.

1034
01:02:08,579 --> 01:02:12,541
Really? Hm? Mmm?

1035
01:02:13,417 --> 01:02:15,294
[laughs]

1036
01:02:15,377 --> 01:02:18,005
What an idiot! Come on, let's go home.

1037
01:02:18,088 --> 01:02:19,089
Gotcha!

1038
01:02:21,258 --> 01:02:23,510
-Can you hold my coconut?
-[music fades]

1039
01:02:23,594 --> 01:02:25,888
[man] Two… three…

1040
01:02:25,971 --> 01:02:30,434
You're making corners,
move smoothly… Three… four.

1041
01:02:32,436 --> 01:02:35,230
Okay, and then you meet in the middle.

1042
01:02:35,814 --> 01:02:37,816
[indistinct chatter]

1043
01:02:39,610 --> 01:02:43,489
[teacher] Okay,
and after, you bow. Okay, go!

1044
01:02:44,072 --> 01:02:45,532
-Rose!
-Really?

1045
01:02:45,616 --> 01:02:47,367
-What are you doing?
-[laughs]

1046
01:02:47,451 --> 01:02:48,744
You don't need to surprise me.

1047
01:02:48,827 --> 01:02:51,747
-I'm fine with hello.
-I just felt like it. You're so serious.

1048
01:02:52,289 --> 01:02:54,541
What are you looking at? You're staring.

1049
01:02:55,709 --> 01:02:57,252
[Rose] That's Juana over there.

1050
01:02:57,336 --> 01:02:59,338
-[teacher] …four, five, six.
-She and her partner…

1051
01:02:59,421 --> 01:03:01,632
They're practicing
the dance for her debut.

1052
01:03:02,132 --> 01:03:06,428
Uh-huh… You're jealous.

1053
01:03:07,930 --> 01:03:11,934
[breathes deeply] No way, Jose.
I'm not jealous…

1054
01:03:12,017 --> 01:03:13,644
[laughs] Don't be jealous!

1055
01:03:14,394 --> 01:03:17,981
Uh… why don't you just
ask him to teach you the dance?

1056
01:03:18,065 --> 01:03:20,359
Uh, okay. Okay, why not?

1057
01:03:20,442 --> 01:03:24,071
But it'll look weird, won't it?
If it's just me doing the practice.

1058
01:03:26,573 --> 01:03:28,700
Well, you have… me.

1059
01:03:30,536 --> 01:03:31,662
Seriously?

1060
01:03:32,162 --> 01:03:35,123
-If you don't want to, you can just say…
-Hey, no taking it back!

1061
01:03:35,207 --> 01:03:36,500
[both laughing]

1062
01:03:37,376 --> 01:03:38,627
Okay. Okay, fine!

1063
01:03:39,628 --> 01:03:41,797
-Uh… Sir?
-Ask him.

1064
01:03:42,464 --> 01:03:45,008
Would we be able to learn to dance?

1065
01:03:45,092 --> 01:03:47,386
-Is that okay?
-Okay. Is he your escort?

1066
01:03:52,099 --> 01:03:53,767
Uh… um, friend.

1067
01:03:55,143 --> 01:03:58,063
-Friend.
-[teacher] Okay, just follow what we do.

1068
01:03:58,856 --> 01:04:00,065
-Stand there.
-[Rose] Okay.

1069
01:04:00,148 --> 01:04:03,151
-[Jordan] I'll go here, yeah.
-[teacher] Okay, ready? Two, nice.

1070
01:04:03,235 --> 01:04:07,739
-Waltz two, three, one, and turn around!
-[teacher] Three, around. And stop, okay.

1071
01:04:07,823 --> 01:04:10,576
-This is Gibo, playing the cajón.
-Okay. Gibo, hey.

1072
01:04:10,659 --> 01:04:12,953
-Yes. And that is Samgi.
-Nice. Hey, Samgi.

1073
01:04:13,036 --> 01:04:14,955
-He will be playing the guitar for us.
-Great.

1074
01:04:15,038 --> 01:04:18,375
While Tony will be playing the macarenas.

1075
01:04:18,458 --> 01:04:20,836
-Macarenas! Go, Tony!
-[Rose laughs] Macarenas.

1076
01:04:20,919 --> 01:04:24,339
And I will be teaching you the song.

1077
01:04:24,423 --> 01:04:27,092
-Let's do this. Okay?
-And Jordan will sing backup.

1078
01:04:27,175 --> 01:04:30,888
-Okay, great, great.
-Hey, I only sing heavy metal!

1079
01:04:30,971 --> 01:04:32,848
-What do you mean, "backup"?
-It'll be great.

1080
01:04:33,348 --> 01:04:36,310
Okay, the first line…
[sings lyrics in Filipino]

1081
01:04:36,393 --> 01:04:39,605
[in English] Hang on, just slower.
Can you break it down?

1082
01:04:39,688 --> 01:04:42,524
-Please, for me.
-You say… [recites lyrics in Filipino]

1083
01:04:42,608 --> 01:04:46,028
-[repeats lyrics in Filipino]
-[Rose in English] Yes!

1084
01:04:46,111 --> 01:04:49,281
-Hooray! Faster, that's the first line.
-First line!

1085
01:04:49,364 --> 01:04:52,951
After you finish learning it,
you have to rehearse it over and over.

1086
01:04:53,035 --> 01:04:54,494
I'll manage Ms. Berta.

1087
01:04:54,578 --> 01:04:57,581
I'll prepare her for the harana
so she doesn't disappear again.

1088
01:04:57,664 --> 01:05:00,584
-How're you going to do that?
-She loves salsa!

1089
01:05:00,667 --> 01:05:01,877
-Really?
-Yeah!

1090
01:05:01,960 --> 01:05:03,462
-Okay!
-Great!

1091
01:05:03,545 --> 01:05:04,504
[all laugh]

1092
01:05:04,588 --> 01:05:05,547
[Rose] Let's go!

1093
01:05:05,631 --> 01:05:07,925
Ewan made that.
He asked me to give it to you.

1094
01:05:08,008 --> 01:05:12,012
-Did he cook it all?
-For you. Because it's your favorite.

1095
01:05:14,598 --> 01:05:17,559
-It's yum! Mmm.
-Nice! Yes!

1096
01:05:18,060 --> 01:05:19,311
-She loved it?
-She loved it.

1097
01:05:19,394 --> 01:05:21,480
-Oh!
-She had a big smile when eating the meal.

1098
01:05:21,563 --> 01:05:22,856
She said the sauce was great!

1099
01:05:22,940 --> 01:05:25,108
Now I can't wait for the surprise.

1100
01:05:25,192 --> 01:05:27,611
Me too! I'm sure she's gonna love it.

1101
01:05:27,694 --> 01:05:30,739
Especially when she sees
you wearing that barong,

1102
01:05:30,822 --> 01:05:32,407
looking all handsome!

1103
01:05:32,491 --> 01:05:35,160
I'm sure she'll run to you in double time!

1104
01:05:35,243 --> 01:05:37,037
-Fingers crossed.
-Yes!

1105
01:05:37,120 --> 01:05:42,960
If you think I look handsome
in this barong, you should see Jordan!

1106
01:05:44,378 --> 01:05:45,545
Way better!

1107
01:05:46,463 --> 01:05:48,465
[intriguing music playing]

1108
01:06:14,992 --> 01:06:17,077
So… how do I look?

1109
01:06:19,204 --> 01:06:20,247
Handsome, sir.

1110
01:06:20,914 --> 01:06:23,041
[friends cheer mockingly]

1111
01:06:23,125 --> 01:06:25,460
-[Tony] Yeah! There she goes again!
-[Gibo] You two! Ah.

1112
01:06:25,544 --> 01:06:30,590
-Oh, to be young and in love!
-[Gibo squeals]

1113
01:06:31,174 --> 01:06:34,302
[Tony] She's totally into him.
Look, she's blushing!

1114
01:06:36,513 --> 01:06:37,639
[music stops]

1115
01:06:37,723 --> 01:06:39,725
[romantic guitar music playing]

1116
01:06:42,310 --> 01:06:43,645
Are you serious?

1117
01:06:50,152 --> 01:06:52,154
[sings a romantic song in Filipino]

1118
01:07:34,029 --> 01:07:36,823
[harmonizing in Filipino]

1119
01:07:53,381 --> 01:07:54,382
[in English] I got this.

1120
01:07:54,466 --> 01:07:57,344
-How do I look… okay? All right.
-You're beautiful.

1121
01:07:57,427 --> 01:07:58,637
-Berta.
-For me?

1122
01:07:58,720 --> 01:08:01,431
-Yes, of course!
-Oh. Thank you!

1123
01:08:01,515 --> 01:08:05,727
-To… RomblonPrettyGirl@skype.com!
-[Berta laughs]

1124
01:08:06,311 --> 01:08:09,856
-That's sweet.
-To the woman… who was there…

1125
01:08:09,940 --> 01:08:12,150
In my computer, every day.

1126
01:08:14,027 --> 01:08:17,322
You have saved me… from my sadness.

1127
01:08:18,323 --> 01:08:23,370
Even though we were countries apart,
I felt your love…

1128
01:08:23,870 --> 01:08:29,376
pass through our computer screens,
straight into my heart.

1129
01:08:29,459 --> 01:08:31,461
[laughs softly through tears]

1130
01:08:34,631 --> 01:08:37,342
[Berta] How do I look? Am I beautiful?

1131
01:08:37,425 --> 01:08:39,427
-[Rose] You are so beautiful.
-Okay.

1132
01:08:41,138 --> 01:08:42,681
[Rose] So, so beautiful.

1133
01:08:43,390 --> 01:08:46,101
-Berta…
-[gasps]

1134
01:08:46,685 --> 01:08:48,645
[crying]

1135
01:08:50,063 --> 01:08:52,858
Will you marry me?

1136
01:09:04,244 --> 01:09:05,287
Go!

1137
01:09:07,706 --> 01:09:10,125
Ewan… Ewan.

1138
01:09:11,501 --> 01:09:12,836
-Yes!
-Yes!

1139
01:09:12,919 --> 01:09:14,629
Yes! Absolutely, yes!

1140
01:09:15,505 --> 01:09:18,175
-Does it fit?
-Oh… perfect!

1141
01:09:18,258 --> 01:09:20,719
-Perfect. Oh, yeah!
-Perfect. Oh, my love!

1142
01:09:21,928 --> 01:09:25,098
[Jordan resumes singing in Filipino]

1143
01:10:09,851 --> 01:10:11,853
[harmonizing in Filipino]

1144
01:10:26,910 --> 01:10:28,328
[song ends]

1145
01:10:35,168 --> 01:10:37,337
-[boys cheering]
-[Gibo in English] Aw, guys! Go home!

1146
01:10:37,420 --> 01:10:38,880
[Jordan laughing]

1147
01:10:40,131 --> 01:10:41,132
[Jordan ] Uh…

1148
01:10:42,509 --> 01:10:43,635
-Rose.
-Jordan.

1149
01:10:43,718 --> 01:10:44,886
[both laugh lightly]

1150
01:10:44,970 --> 01:10:47,973
-[Jordan] You go first.
-No, uh…

1151
01:10:48,056 --> 01:10:50,392
Nothing. I just wanted to say that…

1152
01:10:51,268 --> 01:10:53,395
uh, I loved the way you sang.

1153
01:10:53,895 --> 01:10:59,025
For someone who's a heavy metal rocker,
you could be a balladeer.

1154
01:10:59,526 --> 01:11:01,319
-Really? [laughs]
-You could!

1155
01:11:02,862 --> 01:11:04,990
I honestly didn't think
I could sing like that.

1156
01:11:05,073 --> 01:11:07,742
-Oh! I told you you'd be great.
-Mm. [laughs]

1157
01:11:07,826 --> 01:11:09,119
You wouldn't believe it.

1158
01:11:11,162 --> 01:11:12,205
Thank you.

1159
01:11:13,915 --> 01:11:15,333
Thank you for what?

1160
01:11:16,835 --> 01:11:18,420
For always believing in me.

1161
01:11:21,131 --> 01:11:25,719
Oh, of course, because…
you're paying me, remember?

1162
01:11:26,553 --> 01:11:28,346
Is it really 'cause of the money?

1163
01:11:30,890 --> 01:11:32,183
[Jordan laughs nervously]

1164
01:11:34,269 --> 01:11:35,312
Um…

1165
01:11:37,522 --> 01:11:42,110
Hey. Get off the ground now.
You can't propose. I'm too young for that!

1166
01:11:42,193 --> 01:11:45,238
Oh, yeah, of course.
Of course I know that.

1167
01:11:45,322 --> 01:11:47,490
I am too! [laughs]

1168
01:11:48,325 --> 01:11:49,367
But, um…

1169
01:11:54,748 --> 01:11:56,583
I do have another proposal.

1170
01:11:57,876 --> 01:12:00,045
Proposal? What proposal?

1171
01:12:04,758 --> 01:12:05,800
Rose…

1172
01:12:10,096 --> 01:12:12,515
Can I be your escort at your debut?

1173
01:12:14,100 --> 01:12:17,562
-Are you sure?
-[laughs] Of course I'm sure!

1174
01:12:17,645 --> 01:12:20,231
-Of course. Yes.
-Mm.

1175
01:12:20,982 --> 01:12:23,234
But, um, if you have someone else in mind…

1176
01:12:23,318 --> 01:12:25,653
-Get up now, you're talking too much!
-Please…

1177
01:12:26,154 --> 01:12:28,365
I'll think about it first.

1178
01:12:29,157 --> 01:12:30,784
Think about? Really?

1179
01:12:30,867 --> 01:12:36,289
I mean, come on.
They say… I look like Jack.

1180
01:12:36,790 --> 01:12:37,916
Right?

1181
01:12:39,334 --> 01:12:41,544
You are Rose.

1182
01:12:43,671 --> 01:12:46,925
I'd say we're perfect together.
If you ask me!

1183
01:12:47,008 --> 01:12:49,302
[both laugh]

1184
01:12:49,386 --> 01:12:52,514
Fine, we can be Jack and Rose at my debut!

1185
01:12:52,597 --> 01:12:54,933
-Yeah?
-Yes, but…

1186
01:12:55,558 --> 01:12:58,728
I hope the ending's
not that tragic at my debut.

1187
01:12:58,812 --> 01:13:02,649
[laughs] I hope so! I hope so!

1188
01:13:05,151 --> 01:13:07,445
So, um, what now?

1189
01:13:08,238 --> 01:13:10,156
HHWW?

1190
01:13:12,283 --> 01:13:14,244
I'm sorry, what's that?

1191
01:13:15,412 --> 01:13:17,747
Holding hands while walking.

1192
01:13:20,166 --> 01:13:21,209
Schmaltzy.

1193
01:13:22,293 --> 01:13:24,254
-Huh? Schmaltzy! It's a good word.
-Ugh.

1194
01:13:24,337 --> 01:13:28,508
It's a good word.
Oh, come on. Okay. Hey, hey, hey.

1195
01:13:54,701 --> 01:13:56,035
-Bye-bye!
-Bye!

1196
01:14:00,540 --> 01:14:02,500
-Uh, what… what do I…
-Uh…

1197
01:14:02,584 --> 01:14:06,045
-Do I… What do I do?
-Uh… do?! Stay here. I'll go there.

1198
01:14:06,129 --> 01:14:07,464
-Right. Yeah.
-Okay, yeah!

1199
01:14:11,759 --> 01:14:12,802
Bye.

1200
01:14:13,303 --> 01:14:14,804
-Bye-bye.
-Bye.

1201
01:14:19,058 --> 01:14:21,060
[music swells]

1202
01:14:26,274 --> 01:14:27,442
[laughs nervously]

1203
01:14:28,401 --> 01:14:29,319
Bye!

1204
01:14:36,576 --> 01:14:37,619
[father] Mmm!

1205
01:14:38,745 --> 01:14:42,832
-Mmm…
-[Rose laughs]

1206
01:14:44,083 --> 01:14:47,879
-So this daughter of mine is all grown up?
-Dad!

1207
01:14:47,962 --> 01:14:49,172
[father] Huh?

1208
01:14:49,255 --> 01:14:50,215
[both laugh]

1209
01:14:50,298 --> 01:14:53,593
That guy from the Titanic
and your Jordan are almost the same!

1210
01:14:53,676 --> 01:14:55,929
[both laugh]

1211
01:14:56,012 --> 01:14:58,014
And you, my love? Huh?

1212
01:14:58,097 --> 01:15:01,392
Sorry, Dad. Sorry, Pop.

1213
01:15:01,476 --> 01:15:04,062
You're really very pretty! Huh?

1214
01:15:06,689 --> 01:15:10,193
Come on, Dad, cut me some slack.
Just this once…

1215
01:15:10,276 --> 01:15:11,236
-Okay?
-Mmm.

1216
01:15:11,319 --> 01:15:12,570
Okay.

1217
01:15:13,363 --> 01:15:16,574
But you… can't get pregnant,
you're far too young.

1218
01:15:16,658 --> 01:15:17,742
-Dad!
-Huh?

1219
01:15:17,825 --> 01:15:21,454
-I don't want… No, I won't… Why say it?
-[laughs]

1220
01:15:21,538 --> 01:15:24,207
-I'm joking! [laughs]
-Ugh.

1221
01:15:24,290 --> 01:15:26,209
-Hey, Rose…
-[high-pitched ringing]

1222
01:15:26,709 --> 01:15:28,169
I was joking.

1223
01:15:30,547 --> 01:15:31,589
Rose.

1224
01:15:33,258 --> 01:15:34,259
Rose?

1225
01:15:34,884 --> 01:15:36,970
[tense music playing]

1226
01:15:37,470 --> 01:15:39,556
-[thud]
-Hey, Rose! Hey, Rose?

1227
01:15:40,056 --> 01:15:42,058
[tense music continues]

1228
01:15:44,435 --> 01:15:47,230
[heavy metal music playing
through headphones]

1229
01:15:50,275 --> 01:15:53,611
Jordan! Jordan, Jordan, Jordan!
Look at this!

1230
01:15:53,695 --> 01:15:55,780
I… look at this.
Oh, you're gonna love this.

1231
01:15:55,863 --> 01:15:57,740
-Out of the way.
-Gela, be careful.

1232
01:15:58,575 --> 01:15:59,659
Look at this!

1233
01:15:59,742 --> 01:16:04,581
Everyone in town is talking
about the foreigner and Ms. Berta.

1234
01:16:04,664 --> 01:16:08,459
Then there's you and Rose.
You guys are like real-life Cupids.

1235
01:16:08,543 --> 01:16:10,169
-Mm!
-You're famous now!

1236
01:16:13,590 --> 01:16:15,592
[tense music playing]

1237
01:16:17,302 --> 01:16:18,344
Wait.

1238
01:16:19,762 --> 01:16:21,681
This was Rose's second plan.

1239
01:16:21,764 --> 01:16:23,057
What second plan?

1240
01:16:23,141 --> 01:16:25,184
2. BE FEATURED
IN THE LOCAL NEWSPAPER OF ROMBLON

1241
01:16:25,268 --> 01:16:29,480
Nothing. Um… thank you.
Thank you, Gela. Uh…

1242
01:16:29,564 --> 01:16:31,733
-You're welcome.
-Have you seen Rose, 'cause…

1243
01:16:31,816 --> 01:16:33,901
I haven't seen her all day.
I messaged but no reply.

1244
01:16:33,985 --> 01:16:35,695
Surely she's at Green Skies.

1245
01:16:36,946 --> 01:16:38,489
Most likely, yeah.

1246
01:16:39,282 --> 01:16:42,910
-Rose! Rose! Guys, Rose? Where's Rose?
-Huh?

1247
01:16:42,994 --> 01:16:43,953
-Gibo.
-Jordan.

1248
01:16:44,037 --> 01:16:45,121
Where's Rose?

1249
01:16:46,205 --> 01:16:48,750
-No Rose?
-She's not here.

1250
01:16:48,833 --> 01:16:50,335
[indistinct background chatter]

1251
01:16:50,418 --> 01:16:52,879
-Where is she?
-She's sick.

1252
01:16:53,796 --> 01:16:56,215
-Damn!
-Are you going to use a computer?

1253
01:16:56,799 --> 01:17:00,887
Yeah, one hour.
Um… and I need these scanned.

1254
01:17:01,387 --> 01:17:02,847
Uh, six is free.

1255
01:17:05,183 --> 01:17:07,435
Dad hasn't replied to you yet?

1256
01:17:10,605 --> 01:17:12,357
And Rose hasn't replied.

1257
01:17:13,149 --> 01:17:14,192
Rose?

1258
01:17:15,109 --> 01:17:17,820
Why is that? You have a tiff?

1259
01:17:18,655 --> 01:17:19,697
Did you?

1260
01:17:19,781 --> 01:17:21,282
[rooster crows outside]

1261
01:17:27,163 --> 01:17:28,623
Gibo says she's sick.

1262
01:17:30,375 --> 01:17:31,876
She's sick, but I…

1263
01:17:34,420 --> 01:17:37,715
Hey, Mom… last time I saw her,
I kissed her on the cheek.

1264
01:17:38,591 --> 01:17:39,717
[laughs]

1265
01:17:39,801 --> 01:17:42,261
Do you think I'm being overaggressive?
She's not answering.

1266
01:17:42,845 --> 01:17:44,847
Maybe she's actually sick.

1267
01:17:45,682 --> 01:17:47,433
Have you been by her place?

1268
01:17:49,519 --> 01:17:51,604
-[somber music playing]
-No.

1269
01:17:53,439 --> 01:17:54,816
Go over there.

1270
01:17:56,901 --> 01:17:58,903
[footsteps leaving]

1271
01:18:02,657 --> 01:18:07,161
-[indistinct background chatter]
-[computer game SFX in background]

1272
01:18:12,875 --> 01:18:13,918
[message pings]

1273
01:18:18,381 --> 01:18:20,007
[music turns tense]

1274
01:18:22,635 --> 01:18:24,637
[music turns poignant]

1275
01:18:33,771 --> 01:18:34,814
Oh my God!

1276
01:18:35,815 --> 01:18:38,317
Oh my God! Fuck, yeah! Fuck, yeah.

1277
01:18:38,401 --> 01:18:41,237
-Hey, enough with the "fuck." What's up?
-Sorry. Sorry, sorry.

1278
01:18:42,363 --> 01:18:44,365
[upbeat music continues]

1279
01:18:49,704 --> 01:18:51,289
Rose? Rose!

1280
01:18:52,623 --> 01:18:54,000
[panting]

1281
01:18:56,043 --> 01:18:57,170
[Rose] Jordan?

1282
01:18:57,795 --> 01:19:00,089
Gibo said you're sick. Are you sick?

1283
01:19:01,299 --> 01:19:03,009
I don't know what to tell you.

1284
01:19:05,011 --> 01:19:06,721
I wanted to tell you in person.

1285
01:19:08,055 --> 01:19:09,265
We did it!

1286
01:19:09,348 --> 01:19:10,933
My dad replied.

1287
01:19:12,018 --> 01:19:13,478
My dad replied!

1288
01:19:14,061 --> 01:19:15,605
[gasps] My dad replied, Rose.

1289
01:19:16,606 --> 01:19:21,277
[tearfully] My dad… My dad replied.
He… I didn't think it was possible, but…

1290
01:19:22,570 --> 01:19:26,365
After so long, he finally replied,
and it's all because of you.

1291
01:19:26,449 --> 01:19:28,075
Thank you so much.

1292
01:19:28,576 --> 01:19:32,747
[crying] Thank you, Rose. Thank you.

1293
01:19:33,831 --> 01:19:35,833
We did it! We… [laughs]

1294
01:19:36,459 --> 01:19:40,296
-[tearfully] Congrats!
-What? Why are you crying?

1295
01:19:42,548 --> 01:19:44,550
I'm happy for you.

1296
01:19:45,092 --> 01:19:46,761
[both laugh softly]

1297
01:19:47,678 --> 01:19:49,013
Thank you.

1298
01:19:49,096 --> 01:19:52,266
Thank you.
I… I couldn't have done it without you.

1299
01:19:54,393 --> 01:19:55,770
[father clears throat]

1300
01:19:57,688 --> 01:19:59,065
You're Jordan, right?

1301
01:20:00,441 --> 01:20:01,567
Yeah. Yes, sir.

1302
01:20:01,651 --> 01:20:04,821
Are you hungry?
Why don't you join us out back?

1303
01:20:16,332 --> 01:20:18,376
So you like eating kinilaw, huh?

1304
01:20:21,337 --> 01:20:23,965
-Dad, he's just being respectful.
-[father] Mm?

1305
01:20:24,048 --> 01:20:25,550
No! [laughs nervously]

1306
01:20:25,633 --> 01:20:29,220
-No, sir. Um, it's actually my first time.
-Mm.

1307
01:20:29,971 --> 01:20:32,557
But… I like it a lot. Thank you.

1308
01:20:32,640 --> 01:20:34,225
Suck up! [laughs]

1309
01:20:35,017 --> 01:20:36,018
[all laugh]

1310
01:20:36,102 --> 01:20:38,187
No! Look, look. Mmm.

1311
01:20:39,814 --> 01:20:42,692
He's just pretending, Dad.
Don't believe a thing.

1312
01:20:43,651 --> 01:20:44,902
Sir, where's the restroom?

1313
01:20:44,986 --> 01:20:48,990
Uh, you go in there and it's on the right.
Just through that door.

1314
01:20:49,073 --> 01:20:50,116
Thank you.

1315
01:20:51,284 --> 01:20:54,453
-[footsteps departing]
-[door opens]

1316
01:20:57,373 --> 01:20:58,583
Have you told him yet?

1317
01:21:02,169 --> 01:21:04,171
[somber music playing]

1318
01:21:06,716 --> 01:21:08,134
Now's the time to tell him.

1319
01:21:09,760 --> 01:21:11,762
[somber music continues]

1320
01:21:19,186 --> 01:21:23,399
-This CD's got the playlist for my debut.
-[Jordan] Mmm.

1321
01:21:26,402 --> 01:21:28,404
"My debut playlist."

1322
01:21:29,071 --> 01:21:33,200
Nice. Are there… any GSK songs on it?

1323
01:21:33,910 --> 01:21:36,245
What do you think? Of course there are.

1324
01:21:36,329 --> 01:21:39,498
I'm sure you know "Story."
Heard that one? Sure you have.

1325
01:21:39,582 --> 01:21:42,668
Oh! Makes sense. Yeah, yeah, yeah. Their…

1326
01:21:42,752 --> 01:21:46,297
That's their…
only ballad song on the album.

1327
01:21:46,964 --> 01:21:49,759
Yeah, right.
They're a heavy metal rock band

1328
01:21:49,842 --> 01:21:53,512
that records one ballad song. It sucks!

1329
01:21:54,347 --> 01:21:57,016
I actually call it their sellout era.

1330
01:21:58,601 --> 01:22:00,603
That's why I want it at the debut.

1331
01:22:00,686 --> 01:22:02,939
I can imagine every detail.

1332
01:22:03,022 --> 01:22:04,065
And then…

1333
01:22:05,608 --> 01:22:07,026
I see it all.

1334
01:22:07,109 --> 01:22:12,949
Everything's slo-mo…
And I'm dancing with my escort.

1335
01:22:14,784 --> 01:22:18,120
You mean… me. Right?

1336
01:22:24,460 --> 01:22:26,462
[melancholic music playing]

1337
01:22:41,477 --> 01:22:46,816
Rose. If you don't want me
to be your escort anymore,

1338
01:22:46,899 --> 01:22:48,234
it's… it's okay.

1339
01:22:48,985 --> 01:22:50,403
You can just tell me.

1340
01:22:53,114 --> 01:22:54,740
Is there something wrong?

1341
01:23:01,831 --> 01:23:03,082
Is there something wrong?

1342
01:23:04,917 --> 01:23:06,085
[cries]

1343
01:23:08,254 --> 01:23:09,755
[hesitates]

1344
01:23:17,179 --> 01:23:19,765
I have brain cancer.

1345
01:23:52,006 --> 01:23:53,049
I…

1346
01:23:54,633 --> 01:23:56,886
I just wish there was
something I could do, you know.

1347
01:23:58,262 --> 01:24:00,014
Oh, come on.

1348
01:24:01,515 --> 01:24:02,767
It's all okay.

1349
01:24:05,394 --> 01:24:06,687
I can do it.

1350
01:24:08,939 --> 01:24:10,649
And survive too.

1351
01:24:15,738 --> 01:24:16,781
Rose.

1352
01:24:18,657 --> 01:24:22,036
Rose. Please, remember…

1353
01:24:25,956 --> 01:24:27,833
I'm always here if you need me.

1354
01:24:27,917 --> 01:24:28,959
Okay?

1355
01:24:30,044 --> 01:24:31,212
Promise?

1356
01:24:32,171 --> 01:24:35,716
Don't forget that, yeah? Promise.

1357
01:24:40,638 --> 01:24:42,056
-I'm all right.
-Okay. [sniffles]

1358
01:24:42,556 --> 01:24:44,391
-Yeah, okay. Sure, okay.
-Okay?

1359
01:24:44,475 --> 01:24:45,893
See you.

1360
01:24:46,393 --> 01:24:48,187
-Okay. See you.
-See you.

1361
01:24:48,270 --> 01:24:49,313
See you. [sniffs]

1362
01:24:54,360 --> 01:24:56,362
-[sobbing]
-[melancholic music playing]

1363
01:25:00,908 --> 01:25:02,034
[takes a deep breath]

1364
01:25:49,290 --> 01:25:52,877
[romantic pop ballad playing]

1365
01:26:49,892 --> 01:26:51,894
[music builds]

1366
01:27:18,170 --> 01:27:20,172
[music falls]

1367
01:27:21,173 --> 01:27:23,175
[music builds]

1368
01:27:59,336 --> 01:28:01,338
[music fades]

1369
01:28:08,429 --> 01:28:10,431
[indistinct chatter]

1370
01:28:12,599 --> 01:28:16,437
Look at you! All growing so well!

1371
01:28:17,229 --> 01:28:18,731
You give me strength.

1372
01:28:20,566 --> 01:28:22,651
And you're beautiful as well.

1373
01:28:23,193 --> 01:28:25,362
I want to bloom like you.

1374
01:28:33,412 --> 01:28:35,331
[Ms. Melai] Rose? Rose!

1375
01:28:35,831 --> 01:28:37,416
-Oh, Rose!
-Ms. Melai?

1376
01:28:37,499 --> 01:28:40,210
Rose! [groans]

1377
01:28:41,003 --> 01:28:42,629
I heard the news.

1378
01:28:45,341 --> 01:28:49,094
But I'm not going to cry.
Because you don't like drama, right?

1379
01:28:49,887 --> 01:28:51,013
That's fine!

1380
01:28:51,513 --> 01:28:54,058
So what's the word from the doctor?
Can they make you better?

1381
01:28:55,142 --> 01:28:56,852
[sighs] Uh, well, you know…

1382
01:28:56,935 --> 01:29:01,398
I have a booking next week.
That's so I can begin chemo.

1383
01:29:01,482 --> 01:29:04,693
Because they need to see
how I'll go with the treatment.

1384
01:29:07,404 --> 01:29:10,449
Know what? I am going to make sure

1385
01:29:10,532 --> 01:29:13,160
that all these flowers
get to you at the hospital.

1386
01:29:13,243 --> 01:29:15,079
-Not there, Ms. Melai.
-What?

1387
01:29:15,162 --> 01:29:18,874
The debut party… If I make it!

1388
01:29:18,957 --> 01:29:21,335
-Oh, no! Don't talk like that.
-[laughs]

1389
01:29:21,418 --> 01:29:23,170
You know you're going to get better.

1390
01:29:23,253 --> 01:29:26,715
And then, we'll bring
all these flowers to your debut, huh?

1391
01:29:28,550 --> 01:29:30,302
Give me those. They're mine.

1392
01:29:30,386 --> 01:29:33,764
Because I won't have you
working too hard and becoming exhausted.

1393
01:29:34,556 --> 01:29:37,976
Well, good morning, Star Seekers Company.
I'm Kevin Dimaguiba.

1394
01:29:38,060 --> 01:29:40,270
Ms. Melai, what's going on?

1395
01:29:40,354 --> 01:29:42,106
You wouldn't have heard about that.

1396
01:29:42,189 --> 01:29:45,734
It's people from Channel 3
looking for teenagers to audition.

1397
01:29:45,818 --> 01:29:47,611
-What?
-Those that want to be stars.

1398
01:29:48,195 --> 01:29:49,905
How long are they gonna be here,
Ms. Melai?

1399
01:29:49,988 --> 01:29:53,158
They're here until next week,
then they move to a different location.

1400
01:29:53,242 --> 01:29:56,286
Kevin Dimaguiba.
Vote for me on Star Seekers.

1401
01:29:57,454 --> 01:29:59,957
-[phone rings]
-Yeah, Rose. What's up?

1402
01:30:00,040 --> 01:30:02,167
Hello, Jordan. Is your class over?

1403
01:30:02,751 --> 01:30:04,128
Yeah, what's wrong?

1404
01:30:04,211 --> 01:30:07,798
I think we're ready
to action the third plan on our list.

1405
01:30:10,050 --> 01:30:13,470
[Rose] Your audition
is exactly a week from now, huh?

1406
01:30:14,555 --> 01:30:17,933
Yeah, and your chemo session's
exactly one week from now too.

1407
01:30:18,684 --> 01:30:21,979
[Rose] Hey. Don't worry about that.

1408
01:30:23,522 --> 01:30:25,983
As long as we're prepared, right?

1409
01:30:26,567 --> 01:30:30,404
Because then you'll get in.
And you'll be on TV.

1410
01:30:30,904 --> 01:30:34,283
Tell me,
why do you want to be a celebrity?

1411
01:30:35,492 --> 01:30:37,661
Uh, because I, um…

1412
01:30:37,744 --> 01:30:41,165
Hey, what are you saying?
You can't say "um." Don't give me "um."

1413
01:30:41,248 --> 01:30:43,917
Don't show them you're thinking.
This is the answer, okay?

1414
01:30:44,001 --> 01:30:48,797
"Because my friends tell me
that I am the Leonardo DiCaprio of Romblon

1415
01:30:48,881 --> 01:30:50,215
and I want to be a star!"

1416
01:30:50,299 --> 01:30:52,718
-Okay?
-I don't know why I'm saying that. I…

1417
01:30:52,801 --> 01:30:53,677
-Game!
-Ugh!

1418
01:30:53,760 --> 01:30:55,429
Because my friends tell me

1419
01:30:55,512 --> 01:30:59,516
I'm the Leonardo DiCaprio of Romblon,
and I want to be a star.

1420
01:30:59,600 --> 01:31:01,477
-[Rose] Happy! How do you show happy?
-Happy?

1421
01:31:03,061 --> 01:31:05,731
-There you go!
-Happier, okay. Happier!

1422
01:31:05,814 --> 01:31:08,275
-Woo! Yes!
-Yes, very good!

1423
01:31:08,358 --> 01:31:10,110
-Angry.
-Mad?

1424
01:31:10,194 --> 01:31:13,447
Oh, sure.
Get angry with the camera. That's it!

1425
01:31:13,530 --> 01:31:16,033
-Sadness?
-Sadness.

1426
01:31:17,618 --> 01:31:18,994
Is that the best you can do?

1427
01:31:19,995 --> 01:31:22,873
It should be…
We don't want it looking fake.

1428
01:31:22,956 --> 01:31:26,168
If you're feeling blue,
hit me with it. Okay?

1429
01:31:26,251 --> 01:31:27,544
-Sad.
-Okay.

1430
01:31:27,628 --> 01:31:29,213
Go. Tap into your emotions.

1431
01:31:30,297 --> 01:31:32,299
[music fades]

1432
01:31:36,303 --> 01:31:40,349
-Rose? Rose! Rose! Hey!
-[tense music playing]

1433
01:31:40,432 --> 01:31:42,559
[high-pitched ringing]

1434
01:31:42,643 --> 01:31:44,061
Hey, are you okay?

1435
01:31:46,230 --> 01:31:48,065
[music builds]

1436
01:31:49,733 --> 01:31:51,693
Oh… there.

1437
01:31:52,569 --> 01:31:57,241
That's sadness. See, I felt that.
Now you look incredibly sad.

1438
01:31:57,324 --> 01:31:59,910
Rose, this is stupid.
Why would you do that? Don't do that.

1439
01:32:01,537 --> 01:32:03,997
-[somber music playing]
-Sorry.

1440
01:32:08,418 --> 01:32:12,297
-How would you like your hair done today?
-I don't know.

1441
01:32:12,381 --> 01:32:14,675
-Hey, Berta, it'd be quicker to shave it.
-I could try…

1442
01:32:16,718 --> 01:32:18,845
-Just a bit.
-Like, bald?

1443
01:32:18,929 --> 01:32:21,473
-No. No, no, no. Come on, no way.
-You'd have some hair.

1444
01:32:21,557 --> 01:32:24,142
I don't think
I'd look good as a bald guy, okay?

1445
01:32:24,226 --> 01:32:26,061
It'd give you an awesome look.

1446
01:32:26,144 --> 01:32:29,565
Or, if you want, I could trim it a little.

1447
01:32:29,648 --> 01:32:32,859
-Or I could take it off the top.
-Yeah, I can do a trim.

1448
01:32:32,943 --> 01:32:36,154
-[Berta] You don't want a color?
-No. No, I'm happy with…

1449
01:32:37,447 --> 01:32:39,992
This is fine. Yeah, let's do a trim.

1450
01:32:40,075 --> 01:32:42,786
-A trim'll be fine.
-He's scared to shave, but I'll shave.

1451
01:32:42,869 --> 01:32:45,038
-What are you doing?
-What are you talking about?

1452
01:32:45,122 --> 01:32:46,415
I really want to go bald.

1453
01:32:48,083 --> 01:32:49,835
And why would you do that?

1454
01:32:50,335 --> 01:32:55,173
Well, it'll probably happen anyway.
Why not now?

1455
01:32:59,553 --> 01:33:00,596
Ready.

1456
01:33:01,638 --> 01:33:03,640
[razor buzzing]

1457
01:33:06,351 --> 01:33:09,479
[melancholic music playing]

1458
01:33:15,777 --> 01:33:18,739
[music builds]

1459
01:33:52,439 --> 01:33:54,441
[music fades]

1460
01:33:55,484 --> 01:34:00,364
Psst. So… how do you think I look?

1461
01:34:08,080 --> 01:34:10,165
What? No answer?

1462
01:34:10,666 --> 01:34:13,251
-Don't you like it? Is it bad?
-[laughs softly]

1463
01:34:14,628 --> 01:34:15,879
It's not that.

1464
01:34:17,589 --> 01:34:20,759
What now?
Why are you staring at me like that?

1465
01:34:24,680 --> 01:34:25,722
Well…

1466
01:34:31,436 --> 01:34:33,563
It's 'cause I want to remember this face.

1467
01:34:38,610 --> 01:34:40,195
Bald and perfect.

1468
01:34:45,158 --> 01:34:47,703
Have you eaten something weird?

1469
01:34:47,786 --> 01:34:49,371
-It's Rose!
-[laughs]

1470
01:35:05,178 --> 01:35:06,221
[Jordan] Rose.

1471
01:35:12,102 --> 01:35:14,271
Rose, can I please not do that audition?

1472
01:35:15,856 --> 01:35:16,940
What?

1473
01:35:17,899 --> 01:35:18,942
Why?

1474
01:35:19,443 --> 01:35:23,363
I want to be there with you.
In your chemo sessions.

1475
01:35:30,245 --> 01:35:33,081
-To do what? Wha--
-To… to be there with you.

1476
01:35:35,250 --> 01:35:37,502
To be there with you, to hold your hand.

1477
01:35:38,754 --> 01:35:41,423
Be next to you.
Be next to you through the whole process.

1478
01:35:41,506 --> 01:35:43,967
I want you to know
that I'm here through everything.

1479
01:35:49,806 --> 01:35:51,933
Jordan, that won't help me.

1480
01:35:53,185 --> 01:35:56,146
You can't do a thing. Okay?

1481
01:36:03,403 --> 01:36:06,823
Rose, why are you…
why are you pushing me away, Rose?

1482
01:36:08,074 --> 01:36:10,076
[waves lapping gently]

1483
01:36:11,369 --> 01:36:13,371
[melancholic music playing]

1484
01:36:15,957 --> 01:36:20,796
I'm afraid I won't be able
to survive this. [sobs]

1485
01:36:23,673 --> 01:36:26,802
-I don't want you to see me die.
-Don't say that, don't say that.

1486
01:36:26,885 --> 01:36:30,222
-But it can happen.
-Rose. It can happen, but it won't.

1487
01:36:30,305 --> 01:36:33,266
-But if I do…
-Don't, don't even bring it up, Rose.

1488
01:36:34,851 --> 01:36:36,186
It's not fair.

1489
01:36:36,770 --> 01:36:39,564
We're not going to talk about
you dying because you're not going to die.

1490
01:36:39,648 --> 01:36:42,818
-Shh. Jordan. Jordan!
-You have to hold on. God damn!

1491
01:36:43,944 --> 01:36:45,779
Shhh. [sobs]

1492
01:36:47,447 --> 01:36:48,782
If I do…

1493
01:36:49,407 --> 01:36:54,287
[shakily] If I do…
you have to continue our plans, huh?

1494
01:36:56,248 --> 01:36:58,458
You have to meet your dad.

1495
01:36:59,000 --> 01:37:03,880
You… you need to meet your dad,
and you have to get off this island.

1496
01:37:04,381 --> 01:37:08,176
-Okay? Okay?
-[feebly] Yeah.

1497
01:37:14,099 --> 01:37:16,101
[Jordan crying]

1498
01:37:17,727 --> 01:37:22,107
You know, Jordan, when… when I was young…

1499
01:37:24,818 --> 01:37:27,821
When I was young,
all I wanted was a simple life.

1500
01:37:31,283 --> 01:37:33,159
I just wanted to be alive.

1501
01:37:36,454 --> 01:37:38,874
Here on Romblon. [laughs through tears]

1502
01:37:40,333 --> 01:37:42,836
With my mother… and my dad.

1503
01:37:46,756 --> 01:37:53,013
Before long, when I started to hang out
at the computer shop day in, day out…

1504
01:37:55,599 --> 01:37:59,728
I saw that…
this earth was big and beautiful.

1505
01:37:59,811 --> 01:38:01,271
[breathes deeply]

1506
01:38:01,354 --> 01:38:05,191
And there were so many interesting places…

1507
01:38:06,276 --> 01:38:08,236
outside of this island.

1508
01:38:09,571 --> 01:38:14,993
So… I don't know whether
it seems superficial, but…

1509
01:38:16,828 --> 01:38:19,581
I'd like to have what Mara San Andres had.

1510
01:38:19,664 --> 01:38:21,917
[laughs softly] To be like her.

1511
01:38:22,417 --> 01:38:26,588
I'd like to have the chance
to be a princess. Just for one night.

1512
01:38:30,759 --> 01:38:34,971
I want a debut. I want a debut because…

1513
01:38:35,889 --> 01:38:41,645
I worked and I put my money away.
I saved and worked so hard…

1514
01:38:42,145 --> 01:38:44,981
because I wanted to have a fancy debut.

1515
01:38:45,482 --> 01:38:49,194
Then I hear all the people…
there are lots of people saying,

1516
01:38:49,277 --> 01:38:55,200
"Wow! Oh, wow! You are awesome, Rose.
Did you see Rose? Wasn't she great?!"

1517
01:38:56,034 --> 01:39:00,705
"She had a wonderful debut party.
She did all that, you know."

1518
01:39:00,789 --> 01:39:03,291
"And what about
the way she saved for that?"

1519
01:39:03,375 --> 01:39:05,961
"Because she dreamt about it."

1520
01:39:06,044 --> 01:39:10,048
I just wanted…
I just wanted everyone's attention.

1521
01:39:10,131 --> 01:39:13,969
So that… so that people…

1522
01:39:14,052 --> 01:39:18,556
people would look forward…
to what's next for me.

1523
01:39:22,394 --> 01:39:23,436
But…

1524
01:39:26,439 --> 01:39:28,566
there might be nothing next.

1525
01:39:29,734 --> 01:39:31,945
Maybe there won't be a next.

1526
01:39:32,028 --> 01:39:36,866
Rose, don't. Please don't say that.
Don't say that. Don't be like that.

1527
01:39:36,950 --> 01:39:38,952
[Rose continues crying]

1528
01:39:41,663 --> 01:39:42,747
Jordan…

1529
01:39:43,873 --> 01:39:45,208
If I do…

1530
01:39:47,460 --> 01:39:50,964
you will fulfill your plans, okay?

1531
01:39:51,840 --> 01:39:52,882
Because…

1532
01:39:54,259 --> 01:40:00,390
the moment your dream comes true,
it will be like my dream's come true.

1533
01:40:03,184 --> 01:40:04,394
[sobbing]

1534
01:40:04,894 --> 01:40:06,980
And always remember…

1535
01:40:07,522 --> 01:40:11,860
Don't you forget me, okay?
We did this together.

1536
01:40:13,319 --> 01:40:16,489
-We planned this, me and you.
-[both crying]

1537
01:40:18,074 --> 01:40:21,703
You'll do it, okay? You'll do it.

1538
01:40:29,544 --> 01:40:33,506
Okay. Listen to me.
Listen to me. Listen to me.

1539
01:40:36,426 --> 01:40:37,552
[Rose] Please.

1540
01:40:38,803 --> 01:40:39,846
I'll do it.

1541
01:40:43,808 --> 01:40:45,769
-[laughs through tears]
-I'll do it for you.

1542
01:40:47,520 --> 01:40:49,397
Promise. I promise.

1543
01:40:51,191 --> 01:40:52,358
Thank you.

1544
01:41:02,786 --> 01:41:04,788
[melancholic music continues]

1545
01:41:10,752 --> 01:41:12,754
[indistinct chatter]

1546
01:41:14,380 --> 01:41:15,423
Jordan Anderson.

1547
01:41:21,805 --> 01:41:24,349
-[Rose] Dad, you're sweating so much.
-[laughs]

1548
01:41:24,432 --> 01:41:25,683
Hungry?

1549
01:41:25,767 --> 01:41:29,604
I am, but I'm not allowed to eat.
Nice try, Dad.

1550
01:41:29,687 --> 01:41:31,689
[nurse] Uh, Ms. Rose? Follow me.

1551
01:41:31,773 --> 01:41:34,192
Hello, hello! [laughs nervously] Hello.

1552
01:41:34,901 --> 01:41:36,486
Ma'am, sir, hello.

1553
01:41:36,986 --> 01:41:39,489
My name is Jordan Anderson. 17 years old.

1554
01:41:39,572 --> 01:41:41,866
[melancholic music continues]

1555
01:41:41,950 --> 01:41:43,243
[scanner whirring]

1556
01:41:43,326 --> 01:41:45,328
[melancholic music builds]

1557
01:41:48,790 --> 01:41:49,916
[click]

1558
01:41:57,465 --> 01:41:59,509
-[Rose] Mom!
-[mother] Sweetheart!

1559
01:41:59,592 --> 01:42:02,637
-[Rose screaming in pain]
-What's happened? Where does it hurt?

1560
01:42:02,720 --> 01:42:06,724
-Honey? Rene quickly. Rose, Rose, hold on…
-[continues screaming]

1561
01:42:06,808 --> 01:42:09,936
[mother] The pain will go away.
Just hold on to Mom, okay?

1562
01:42:10,019 --> 01:42:13,773
-Rene! Nurse, please, Rose…
-Mommy!

1563
01:42:13,857 --> 01:42:15,525
-Mom's here by your side.
-What is it?

1564
01:42:15,608 --> 01:42:18,111
-It just hurts too much!
-[screaming]

1565
01:42:18,903 --> 01:42:21,906
[mother] Call the nurse! I'm here, honey.

1566
01:42:22,866 --> 01:42:24,826
[melancholic music continues]

1567
01:42:35,753 --> 01:42:38,298
-[melancholic music fades]
-Thank you, Mom.

1568
01:42:39,299 --> 01:42:43,303
I'm glad you could be here.
Thank you. Thank you.

1569
01:42:43,386 --> 01:42:46,681
Of course, darling,
I don't like working away from here.

1570
01:42:46,764 --> 01:42:52,145
Taking care of folks I'm not close to.
My baby needs me right here with her.

1571
01:42:57,692 --> 01:43:01,738
But, Mom… I haven't got any cash.

1572
01:43:02,238 --> 01:43:05,283
If you were to charge me, I couldn't pay.

1573
01:43:05,366 --> 01:43:07,035
[both laugh]

1574
01:43:07,118 --> 01:43:08,494
I can't afford you.

1575
01:43:09,287 --> 01:43:13,208
You know, Rose, you just get well.
That's more than enough for me.

1576
01:43:13,708 --> 01:43:16,044
-[TV show theme tune plays]
-Can you do that?

1577
01:43:16,127 --> 01:43:17,837
-Yum, thanks.
-Eat up.

1578
01:43:18,463 --> 01:43:19,589
Promise?

1579
01:43:19,672 --> 01:43:22,175
Oh, oh! Jordan, it's Jordan. Jordan's on.

1580
01:43:22,258 --> 01:43:26,054
-Is that your boyfriend?
-No, Mom. He's just my friend.

1581
01:43:28,389 --> 01:43:29,599
Wow!

1582
01:43:29,682 --> 01:43:31,017
[all laugh]

1583
01:43:31,100 --> 01:43:32,310
Dad!

1584
01:43:32,393 --> 01:43:35,230
-[theme tune continues on TV]
-[studio audience cheering]

1585
01:43:39,525 --> 01:43:44,197
We're back
and you're watching Star Seekers.

1586
01:43:45,031 --> 01:43:49,702
And now, we're down
to our last contestant for the night.

1587
01:43:49,786 --> 01:43:53,289
And this kid's popular support
has been off the charts.

1588
01:43:53,373 --> 01:43:54,457
[raucous cheering]

1589
01:43:54,540 --> 01:43:58,586
From the auditions
to here at regional finals,

1590
01:43:58,670 --> 01:44:01,089
his support has been amazing.

1591
01:44:01,589 --> 01:44:04,676
Even the text votes
have been record-breaking.

1592
01:44:04,759 --> 01:44:07,011
Let's not delay any longer.

1593
01:44:07,095 --> 01:44:12,850
Ladies and gentlemen,
the so-called "Jack of Romblon."

1594
01:44:13,643 --> 01:44:15,186
Jordan Anderson!

1595
01:44:15,270 --> 01:44:19,107
[cheering raucously]

1596
01:44:19,190 --> 01:44:21,818
-[theme tune continues]
-[raucous cheering]

1597
01:44:22,568 --> 01:44:27,240
-Look! Excited?
-I'm being supportive, that's all.

1598
01:44:27,824 --> 01:44:32,704
Do you think you are
the star we're searching for?

1599
01:44:33,746 --> 01:44:35,623
Of course. The one and only.

1600
01:44:35,707 --> 01:44:39,002
[TV host] Wow, confidence. I love that.

1601
01:44:39,085 --> 01:44:42,380
-Jordan's handsome. Well done, Jordan.
-I taught Jordan that. I did!

1602
01:44:42,463 --> 01:44:45,800
Your question will be coming
from the one and only,

1603
01:44:45,883 --> 01:44:47,593
-Ms. Mara San Andres.
-[cheering]

1604
01:44:48,469 --> 01:44:51,139
Hi, Jordan. You're so good-looking.

1605
01:44:51,973 --> 01:44:55,518
-Ah! Your idol! Your idol!
-Is she the one, the one that…

1606
01:44:55,601 --> 01:44:58,146
-That's who… that's who's on my mirror.
-Yeah. Oh…

1607
01:44:58,229 --> 01:45:00,398
-Of course, I know who that is.
-That's her face!

1608
01:45:01,065 --> 01:45:03,151
Could you be in a love team?

1609
01:45:03,234 --> 01:45:04,861
[Rose laughs uncomfortably]

1610
01:45:04,944 --> 01:45:07,572
-Kidding! [laughs]
-[audience woos]

1611
01:45:07,655 --> 01:45:09,991
-[audience chattering]
-[laughs nervously] Um…

1612
01:45:10,575 --> 01:45:13,911
-I'm sorry, but… I can't.
-[audience reacts with disappointment]

1613
01:45:15,246 --> 01:45:16,998
[host] Oh, wow.

1614
01:45:17,498 --> 01:45:22,295
This is the first time
I've ever heard anyone reject Ms. Mara.

1615
01:45:23,296 --> 01:45:25,757
Is someone waiting for you in Romblon?

1616
01:45:26,966 --> 01:45:30,345
Anyway, the question
on everyone's mind, Jordan.

1617
01:45:30,845 --> 01:45:33,097
Do you already have a girlfriend?

1618
01:45:33,181 --> 01:45:37,101
-[suspenseful music playing]
-No. No, he won't.

1619
01:45:37,185 --> 01:45:38,853
[suspenseful music continues]

1620
01:45:39,437 --> 01:45:42,065
Girlfriend? [laughs nervously] Um…

1621
01:45:45,360 --> 01:45:46,402
I don't have a girlfriend.

1622
01:45:46,486 --> 01:45:48,196
[TV audience reacts with shock]

1623
01:45:50,114 --> 01:45:55,203
But… someone very special to me
is waiting in Romblon.

1624
01:45:55,286 --> 01:45:56,412
-Oh!
-Mm?

1625
01:45:56,496 --> 01:45:58,498
[tender music playing]

1626
01:46:00,833 --> 01:46:03,169
She's actually a big fan of yours, Mara.

1627
01:46:03,252 --> 01:46:07,715
Oh? Well, she must be very special
for you to reject me

1628
01:46:07,799 --> 01:46:09,509
on national television.

1629
01:46:10,635 --> 01:46:12,178
But she says she's a fan of mine,

1630
01:46:12,261 --> 01:46:16,391
which suggests
she must have pretty good taste.

1631
01:46:18,017 --> 01:46:21,312
Well, anyway, Jordan,
here's my question for you.

1632
01:46:21,896 --> 01:46:25,566
Why do you want to become a star?

1633
01:46:26,359 --> 01:46:29,237
[tender music continues]

1634
01:46:37,453 --> 01:46:39,288
To fulfil a friend's dream.

1635
01:46:40,373 --> 01:46:44,460
I only realized recently
how short life can be.

1636
01:46:45,461 --> 01:46:47,130
You never know when it's your time.

1637
01:46:51,050 --> 01:46:53,886
And in this lifetime, if I have the means…

1638
01:46:53,970 --> 01:46:56,431
If there's a way
to make other people happy…

1639
01:46:58,266 --> 01:46:59,392
why wouldn't I?

1640
01:47:00,351 --> 01:47:02,395
[melancholic music playing]

1641
01:47:05,273 --> 01:47:07,191
If by becoming a star,

1642
01:47:08,651 --> 01:47:11,696
I'll help her realize her happiness…

1643
01:47:14,365 --> 01:47:17,910
then that's my dream… To make her happy.

1644
01:47:19,078 --> 01:47:21,080
[melancholic music builds]

1645
01:47:28,963 --> 01:47:33,968
And the regional winner for Cebu
is none other than…

1646
01:47:34,677 --> 01:47:38,723
-[audience cheering]
-[host] Jordan Anderson!

1647
01:47:39,223 --> 01:47:42,393
3. BECOME FAMOUS AND BE SEEN ON TV

1648
01:47:43,394 --> 01:47:45,980
[audience cheering]

1649
01:47:47,857 --> 01:47:51,736
-[cheering stops]
-[music fades]

1650
01:47:51,819 --> 01:47:54,071
[keyboard clacking]

1651
01:47:57,992 --> 01:47:58,910
[clack]

1652
01:48:04,248 --> 01:48:05,666
[message alert]

1653
01:48:14,967 --> 01:48:16,344
[phone ringing]

1654
01:48:20,806 --> 01:48:24,435
-Jordan?
-[Jordan laughs] Rose, hey!

1655
01:48:25,102 --> 01:48:28,147
Jordan! How is the Jack of Romblon?

1656
01:48:28,231 --> 01:48:34,111
[laughs] I'm good, I'm good.
How is Rose of Romblon? Did you watch?

1657
01:48:34,862 --> 01:48:38,032
-Oh, of course! Of course I did!
-[laughs]

1658
01:48:38,115 --> 01:48:40,493
You were looking great on TV.

1659
01:48:40,576 --> 01:48:45,581
[laughs] Really?
More handsome in person or on TV?

1660
01:48:46,666 --> 01:48:47,708
TV.

1661
01:48:48,376 --> 01:48:50,378
[melancholic music playing]

1662
01:48:51,087 --> 01:48:52,088
But…

1663
01:48:55,633 --> 01:48:57,468
I miss you in person.

1664
01:49:00,263 --> 01:49:04,850
Oh man, I miss you too much.
If only you knew.

1665
01:49:05,810 --> 01:49:07,979
What time is it?
You don't have to sleep yet?

1666
01:49:08,646 --> 01:49:11,399
What? Come on.

1667
01:49:11,899 --> 01:49:16,028
You just called me,
and you think I should go already?

1668
01:49:16,862 --> 01:49:18,155
Why?

1669
01:49:19,365 --> 01:49:24,996
When I'm knocked out,
you think the cancer's knocked out?

1670
01:49:27,206 --> 01:49:28,874
[both laugh]

1671
01:49:28,958 --> 01:49:31,043
You know, I pray for you every day.

1672
01:49:32,670 --> 01:49:34,505
I pray that you'll get better.

1673
01:49:35,464 --> 01:49:39,260
Don't get so serious. Everything's fine.

1674
01:49:39,760 --> 01:49:43,055
♪ I'm alive, alert
Awake, enthusiastic! ♪

1675
01:49:43,139 --> 01:49:44,557
[both laugh]

1676
01:49:45,891 --> 01:49:52,565
But thank you. Thank you, Jordan.
It's so nice to have this break.

1677
01:49:55,276 --> 01:49:57,862
How's your, um, chemo sessions going?

1678
01:50:00,323 --> 01:50:01,574
Okay!

1679
01:50:03,534 --> 01:50:06,162
-Yeah?
-Okay, so far.

1680
01:50:07,246 --> 01:50:11,751
It's all okay.
I'm down to my last session.

1681
01:50:11,834 --> 01:50:13,836
-Yeah.
-Yeah.

1682
01:50:14,337 --> 01:50:15,546
Next week…

1683
01:50:17,131 --> 01:50:18,799
March 25th.

1684
01:50:20,509 --> 01:50:22,511
-On your birthday?
-Yes.

1685
01:50:23,512 --> 01:50:25,890
But… how about your debut?

1686
01:50:26,766 --> 01:50:27,808
Huh?

1687
01:50:30,102 --> 01:50:32,021
-Debut?
-Yeah.

1688
01:50:32,521 --> 01:50:34,815
Uh… On that subject…

1689
01:50:35,524 --> 01:50:37,360
Plans changed!

1690
01:50:38,194 --> 01:50:40,988
We'll just do something nice
at the hospital.

1691
01:50:43,991 --> 01:50:48,663
Uh, man, I wish I could be there for you.
But… you know that…

1692
01:50:50,456 --> 01:50:55,252
I… well… Now, don't worry about that.

1693
01:50:56,212 --> 01:51:00,383
The best birthday gift I could have

1694
01:51:01,175 --> 01:51:04,762
would be if you won Star Seekers.

1695
01:51:05,596 --> 01:51:08,849
-[both laugh]
-I will. I will, I promise.

1696
01:51:09,517 --> 01:51:12,645
Uh, but, hey, by the way,
my dad's been answering all my emails.

1697
01:51:13,604 --> 01:51:15,481
-He's so proud of me. Yeah!
-Really?

1698
01:51:16,232 --> 01:51:19,985
-Oh, good for you. Good job, Jordan.
-[laughs]

1699
01:51:20,069 --> 01:51:22,196
Oh, and what's he say?

1700
01:51:23,698 --> 01:51:25,408
Will he bring you over?

1701
01:51:27,451 --> 01:51:28,786
Yeah.

1702
01:51:28,869 --> 01:51:32,331
He said he'll be my manager if I win,
so we can be together.

1703
01:51:32,415 --> 01:51:35,292
Good job. I told you, right?

1704
01:51:35,376 --> 01:51:39,755
I was convinced that this plan would work.
And it did work, right?

1705
01:51:39,839 --> 01:51:41,006
Yeah.

1706
01:51:41,882 --> 01:51:43,509
Hey, you can never be too sure, huh?

1707
01:51:43,592 --> 01:51:46,887
I don't know, he might
have said that as a joke or something.

1708
01:51:46,971 --> 01:51:51,308
Boy. What's the matter with you?
What did I say to you?

1709
01:51:51,392 --> 01:51:56,522
Remember. I said you should…
never be negative, always be positive.

1710
01:51:56,605 --> 01:51:58,858
Concentrate on the positive side.

1711
01:52:01,569 --> 01:52:05,448
Yeah. I will, I will.
I promise it's all for you, Rose.

1712
01:52:05,531 --> 01:52:06,907
It's all because of you.

1713
01:52:07,908 --> 01:52:10,453
I'm so sorry
I can't make it to your birthday.

1714
01:52:11,120 --> 01:52:14,206
Hey… I feel so guilty.

1715
01:52:15,750 --> 01:52:17,418
Well, it's fine.

1716
01:52:19,420 --> 01:52:21,756
Don't think about it, it's nothing.

1717
01:52:23,507 --> 01:52:27,011
And I'll be able to watch you from the…

1718
01:52:27,511 --> 01:52:30,306
the hospital bed, so… that's fun.

1719
01:52:30,389 --> 01:52:33,434
And after, you can text.

1720
01:52:34,727 --> 01:52:37,980
-[Jordan crying]
-Send me a… picture message.

1721
01:52:38,063 --> 01:52:42,318
-Yeah. Yeah, yeah. Yeah.
-So…

1722
01:52:42,401 --> 01:52:45,905
So, you got to go because my dad's awake.

1723
01:52:46,572 --> 01:52:49,617
He'll probably scold me. Tell me…

1724
01:52:50,743 --> 01:52:54,246
Tell me I'm up too late.
Good night, I'm going now.

1725
01:52:54,330 --> 01:52:57,708
Good night.
You take care, okay? Good night.

1726
01:52:58,417 --> 01:52:59,460
Good night.

1727
01:53:00,920 --> 01:53:01,962
Night.

1728
01:53:06,634 --> 01:53:08,636
[melancholic music continues]

1729
01:53:14,809 --> 01:53:16,936
-[nurse 1] See you. Happy birthday.
-Bye. Thank you.

1730
01:53:17,770 --> 01:53:20,648
-[nurse 2] Good morning. Happy birthday.
-Thank you, nurse.

1731
01:53:21,232 --> 01:53:23,442
So many people are greeting you.

1732
01:53:23,943 --> 01:53:26,111
-Happy birthday.
-Thank you, Mom.

1733
01:53:28,489 --> 01:53:30,324
-[guard] Goodbye.
-[mother] Bye-bye.

1734
01:53:30,825 --> 01:53:35,246
-[Tess] Rose! Happy birthday!
-Hi! Thank you, but…

1735
01:53:36,372 --> 01:53:38,165
-Hello!
-[Tess] Hey.

1736
01:53:38,249 --> 01:53:40,376
What are you doing here?

1737
01:53:41,001 --> 01:53:43,254
Um… giving you a ride.

1738
01:53:44,046 --> 01:53:48,175
[laughs] Tell me… where are we going?

1739
01:53:48,843 --> 01:53:50,636
Maybe just come along.

1740
01:53:52,179 --> 01:53:54,139
-Where?
-Rose, it's all right.

1741
01:53:54,223 --> 01:53:56,684
-This'll be all right?
-[Tess] Yes! Yes, come on!

1742
01:53:57,184 --> 01:53:59,186
[pensive music playing]

1743
01:53:59,895 --> 01:54:03,482
Ms. Berta, what's this about?

1744
01:54:03,566 --> 01:54:05,401
I'm sure I told you

1745
01:54:05,484 --> 01:54:09,154
that I'd be doing your makeup
before your debut.

1746
01:54:09,780 --> 01:54:11,198
Oh, Ms. Berta.

1747
01:54:11,282 --> 01:54:13,742
The celebration's
only going to be at the hospital.

1748
01:54:14,743 --> 01:54:17,830
-We're not going to let that happen.
-There's no way.

1749
01:54:17,913 --> 01:54:20,958
-Not a chance. [laughs]
-[indistinct]

1750
01:54:21,709 --> 01:54:23,460
-But--
-You're asking too many questions.

1751
01:54:23,544 --> 01:54:24,628
Just sit back

1752
01:54:24,712 --> 01:54:28,883
and let us make you look
like the most beautiful girl of Romblon.

1753
01:54:30,426 --> 01:54:31,468
Okay?

1754
01:54:31,552 --> 01:54:34,138
[uplifting music playing]

1755
01:54:47,985 --> 01:54:50,195
I look amazing, Ms. Berta!

1756
01:54:50,696 --> 01:54:56,744
-You're so beautiful, Rose.
-You're blooming just like a flower. Mm.

1757
01:54:56,827 --> 01:55:00,998
-[Gela] You're incredible, Ms. Berta.
-[Berta] This was so easy.

1758
01:55:01,081 --> 01:55:03,083
[uneasy music playing]

1759
01:55:04,543 --> 01:55:08,631
But… something's not right.

1760
01:55:09,173 --> 01:55:12,009
What's wrong? Are the eyebrows even?

1761
01:55:13,177 --> 01:55:14,094
They look fine.

1762
01:55:14,929 --> 01:55:15,930
[Berta] Mm.

1763
01:55:17,890 --> 01:55:19,183
[uneasy music fades]

1764
01:55:21,685 --> 01:55:23,687
[inspiring music playing]

1765
01:55:33,864 --> 01:55:34,907
Perfect.

1766
01:55:36,283 --> 01:55:37,326
Lovely.

1767
01:55:39,078 --> 01:55:40,496
It's all good now.

1768
01:55:41,080 --> 01:55:43,248
-Perfect.
-So lovely.

1769
01:55:47,169 --> 01:55:51,715
-Will my parents be here to see me?
-Of course they will be.

1770
01:55:53,968 --> 01:55:57,805
-Is my dress all right?
-It's fine. You look gorgeous.

1771
01:55:58,305 --> 01:56:00,641
-[Rose] Perfect?
-[Gela] Perfect.

1772
01:56:00,724 --> 01:56:02,726
[uplifting music playing]

1773
01:56:35,592 --> 01:56:37,594
[uplifting music continues]

1774
01:56:52,526 --> 01:56:54,194
Happy birthday, Rose.

1775
01:56:55,362 --> 01:56:57,197
I wasn't expecting to see you.

1776
01:56:57,281 --> 01:56:59,700
I said I would be your escort, right?

1777
01:57:02,578 --> 01:57:03,620
But…

1778
01:57:04,163 --> 01:57:09,168
What about the competition?
The dream and your…

1779
01:57:09,251 --> 01:57:11,253
Dreams can wait for another day.

1780
01:57:12,921 --> 01:57:14,923
But you only turn 18 once…

1781
01:57:15,924 --> 01:57:17,926
And I wouldn't miss that for the world.

1782
01:57:23,432 --> 01:57:24,516
Shall we?

1783
01:57:27,102 --> 01:57:28,771
-[Rose] We shall.
-We shall!

1784
01:57:29,271 --> 01:57:32,191
[uplifting music continues]

1785
01:58:11,146 --> 01:58:13,148
[uplifting music continues]

1786
01:59:11,415 --> 01:59:12,875
[uplifting music builds]

1787
02:00:27,616 --> 02:00:30,452
[Rose] Thank you so much
for organizing this.

1788
02:00:32,162 --> 02:00:35,874
Thank you so much for organizing my life.

1789
02:00:35,958 --> 02:00:37,292
[both laugh]

1790
02:00:37,376 --> 02:00:38,418
Schmaltzy!

1791
02:00:39,169 --> 02:00:40,712
[both laugh]

1792
02:00:40,796 --> 02:00:41,838
Come on.

1793
02:00:42,881 --> 02:00:45,467
Can you let me be romantic just for once?

1794
02:00:47,052 --> 02:00:49,221
Okay, fine!

1795
02:00:50,389 --> 02:00:52,849
Well, my Rose…

1796
02:00:54,393 --> 02:00:55,811
I just wanted to say…

1797
02:00:59,439 --> 02:01:02,776
I found a home here in Romblon
because of you.

1798
02:01:04,861 --> 02:01:07,656
I look forward
to the slow Internet connection.

1799
02:01:10,284 --> 02:01:14,454
Countless days at Green Skies,
the sunsets, everything.

1800
02:01:16,498 --> 02:01:19,209
Because of you,
I've met some of the most amazing people

1801
02:01:19,293 --> 02:01:20,919
I've met in my whole life.

1802
02:01:21,420 --> 02:01:22,629
More than that…

1803
02:01:25,173 --> 02:01:27,217
You've made me realize that…

1804
02:01:29,636 --> 02:01:33,557
I love you so much more
than my American dream.

1805
02:01:36,018 --> 02:01:39,688
[in Filipino] I love you so much, Rose.

1806
02:01:39,771 --> 02:01:42,065
[Rose sobs]

1807
02:01:42,149 --> 02:01:44,443
-[in English] That's enough words for now.
-[laughs]

1808
02:01:44,985 --> 02:01:48,655
-May I talk?
-Of course. Of course.

1809
02:01:49,990 --> 02:01:51,867
I love you, my Jack.

1810
02:01:52,367 --> 02:01:54,661
-I love you.
-I love you.

1811
02:01:54,745 --> 02:01:56,330
-I love you.
-I love you.

1812
02:02:02,502 --> 02:02:05,047
[uplifting music continues]

1813
02:03:06,525 --> 02:03:08,235
[music fades]

1814
02:03:14,866 --> 02:03:16,868
[indistinct background chatter]

1815
02:03:41,393 --> 02:03:43,395
[melancholic music playing]

1816
02:03:48,984 --> 02:03:50,610
It'll be fine.

1817
02:03:52,070 --> 02:03:52,988
Mm?

1818
02:03:53,071 --> 02:03:54,364
[laughs softly]

1819
02:04:11,381 --> 02:04:12,716
Take care.

1820
02:04:27,355 --> 02:04:29,357
[melancholic music continues]

1821
02:05:08,396 --> 02:05:10,398
[music builds]

1822
02:06:49,914 --> 02:06:51,916
[music continues]

1823
02:07:42,592 --> 02:07:44,594
[melancholic music stops]

1824
02:07:44,678 --> 02:07:46,680
[uplifting music playing]

1825
02:09:17,771 --> 02:09:19,773
[music continues]

1826
02:10:33,680 --> 02:10:35,682
[music stops]
